{"_id":"473c68193cb5df26","name":"Grappling Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you hit with a melee attack, you may initiate a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity.","prerequisite":"Base attack bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Grappling Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"When you hit with a melee attack, you may initiate a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"]}}}
{"_id":"477b62d36e012719","name":"Separatist Military Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While you are adjacent to at least one of your allies, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on any one attack roll you make on your turn.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":27,"tags":["ally_support","background_opportunity","faction_training","feat","general","military","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Separatist_Military_Training</p>\n<p>You have received extensive training from the military of The Confederacy of Independent Systems and are familiar with its practices.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>While you are adjacent to at least one of your allies, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on any one attack roll you make on your turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["proximity.ally-nearby"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Separatist Military Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a +1 bonus on an attack roll while adjacent to an ally.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Separatist_Military_Training"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.ally-nearby"],"id":"swse.feat.separatist_military_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Separatist_Military_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4788389dadb5cb0a","name":"Stay Up","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, when you would normally take damage from an attack, you can instead choose to take half damage and move -1 step along the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"Trained in Endurance","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":28,"tags":["condition_track","defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stay_Up</p>\n<p>You can soldier on in spite of damage dealt to you.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Endurance</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Once per encounter, when you would normally take damage from an attack, you can instead choose to take half damage and move -1 step along the Condition Track.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"35df8faa4878f2c5"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Stay Up"}]},"resourceRules":{"conditionTrack":[{"type":"SPEND_CT_TO_REDUCE_DAMAGE","damageReduction":10}]},"shortSummary":"Move 1 step down Condition Track to reduce damage.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Endurance","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stay_Up"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.stay_up","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stay_Up","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"47c92eae6c1a0b84","name":"Pinpoint Accuracy","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Aiming Accuracy Feat, a target you damage cannot take the Recover Action until the end of its next turn.","prerequisite":"Droid, Aiming Accuracy, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":24,"tags":["condition_track","control","feat","general","grapple"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger&#x27;s Guide to Droids</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pinpoint_Accuracy</p>\n<p>This improved version of the Aiming Accuracy Feat moves your enemy -1 step on the Condition Track.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid, Aiming Accuracy, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When using the Aiming Accuracy Feat, a target you damage cannot take the Recover Action until the end of its next turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Pinpoint Accuracy"}]},"shortSummary":"Move target -1 step on the Condition Track when you hit with Aiming Accuracy.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Aiming Accuracy, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pinpoint_Accuracy"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.pinpoint_accuracy","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pinpoint_Accuracy","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"47f21e32233bb910","name":"Resurgent Vitality","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain additional Hit Points when catching a Second Wind.","prerequisite":"Wookiee","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["defense","durability","feat","hit_points","racial","recovery","second_wind","species","species_opportunity","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-wookiee"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain additional Hit Points when catching a Second Wind."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Resurgent Vitality"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain additional Hit Points when catching a Second Wind."},"effects":[{"_id":"6bd1b831-e5a0-42d5-9bfa-a2dd3dbfda4c","name":"Resurgent Vitality","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Resurgent Vitality","effectType":"bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.resurgent_vitality"}}}
{"_id":"4be60753991eec43","name":"Rapid Assault","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you are wielding two weapons or a weapon with which you can use the Double Attack feat, you may spend a Force Point to make two attacks as a Standard Action.\n\nThe normal penalties due to attacking with two weapons or using Double Attack still apply, and you cannot make more than two attacks regardless of how many extra attacks you can make during a Full Attack Action.","prerequisite":"Double Attack or Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"You can only make multiple attacks with the Full Attack Action (a Full-Round Action).","sourcebook":"Web Enhancements","page":1,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Web Enhancements (Saga Edition FAQ (E2))</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Assault</p>\n<p>This section contains Optional Rules that modify gameplay in a significant manner. Whether or not the rules will be utilized is the prerogative of the Gamemaster.</p>\n<p>Through focus and raw determination, you can make multiple attacks even after moving.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Double Attack or Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you are wielding two weapons or a weapon with which you can use the Double Attack feat, you may spend a Force Point to make two attacks as a Standard Action.</p>\n<p>The normal penalties due to attacking with two weapons or using Double Attack still apply, and you cannot make more than two attacks regardless of how many extra attacks you can make during a Full Attack Action.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>You can only make multiple attacks with the Full Attack Action (a Full-Round Action).</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Rapid Assault"}]},"shortSummary":"Through focus and raw determination, you can make multiple attacks even after moving.","prerequisitesText":"Double Attack or Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Web Enhancements (Saga Edition FAQ (E2))"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Assault"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.rapid_assault","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Assault","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4cc4f4afdcf6e4f8","name":"Collateral Damage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you deal damage with a single, non- Area Attack using the Rapid Shot Feat, once per turn on your turn, you can immediately make a second attack at a -2 penalty against a second target within 2 squares of the first. If this attack hits, you deal half the original attack's damage to that target.","prerequisite":"Rapid Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":20,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Collateral_Damage</p>\n<p>Your hail of fire can catch secondary targets in your firing arc.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rapid Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you deal damage with a single, non- Area Attack using the Rapid Shot Feat, once per turn on your turn, you can immediately make a second attack at a -2 penalty against a second target within 2 squares of the first. If this attack hits, you deal half the original attack&#x27;s damage to that target.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":6}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Collateral Damage"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain extra attack upon hitting the first target.","prerequisitesText":"Rapid Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Collateral_Damage"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.collateral_damage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Collateral_Damage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4d6a68d553fb0449","name":"Running Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When making an attack with a melee or ranged weapon, you can move both before and after the attack, provided that the total distance moved is not greater than your Speed.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["feat","general","hit_and_run","mobility","move_action","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958","f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Running_Attack</p>\n<p>You can move as you attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When making an attack with a melee or ranged weapon, you can move both before and after the attack, provided that the total distance moved is not greater than your Speed.</p>\n<h4>Additional Running Attack Effects</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p>Combined Feat (Dodge): You can add your dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense against anyone who makes an Attack of Opportunity against you while using the Running Attack Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Running Attack: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"runningAttack","label":"Running Attack","control":"flag","summary":"Movement-dependent option exposed as a flag; movement validation is not automated yet."}]},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"Move before and after making an attack.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Running_Attack"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged","turn.on-current-turn"],"id":"swse.feat.running_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Running_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4dc36deda6faf597","name":"Anointed Hunter","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you end your Move at least 2 squares from where you started, you gain a +1 competence bonus on attacks made with Thrown Weapons until the end of your turn.","prerequisite":"Nelvaanian","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":20,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Anointed_Hunter</p>\n<p>You have been anointed as a hunter for your tribe and possess skills few other Nelvaanians do.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Nelvaanian</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you end your Move at least 2 squares from where you started, you gain a +1 competence bonus on attacks made with Thrown Weapons until the end of your turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Anointed Hunter"}]},"shortSummary":"Move 2 or more squares and gain a +1 bonus on attacks with Thrown Weapons until the end of your turn.","prerequisitesText":"Nelvaanian","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Anointed_Hunter"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.anointed_hunter","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Anointed_Hunter","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4e57ee834c301ad8","name":"Extra Second Wind","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can catch your Second Wind one additional time per day, but you can still only catch a Second Wind once per encounter.","prerequisite":"Trained in Endurance","special":"You can take this Feat multiple times; each time you take this Feat, you can catch a Second Wind one additional time per day. A Nonheroic character that takes this Feat for the first time can catch a Second Wind once per day.","normalText":"A hero can normally catch his or her Second Wind only once per day.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","recovery","second_wind","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Second_Wind</p>\n<p>You tend to come back from the edge of oblivion more often.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Endurance</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can catch your Second Wind one additional time per day, but you can still only catch a Second Wind once per encounter.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>A hero can normally catch his or her Second Wind only once per day.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can take this Feat multiple times; each time you take this Feat, you can catch a Second Wind one additional time per day. A Nonheroic character that takes this Feat for the first time can catch a Second Wind once per day.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"35df8faa4878f2c5"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RESOURCE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Extra Second Wind"}],"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"EXTRA_DAILY_USE_MULTIPLIER","value":1,"description":"Gain an additional Second Wind use per day/recovery cycle."}]}},"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"EXTRA_DAILY_USE_MULTIPLIER","value":1}]},"shortSummary":"Gain an additional Second Wind per day.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Endurance","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Second_Wind"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.extra_second_wind","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Second_Wind","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4eed406661d3313f","name":"Delay Damage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you may delay the effects of damage taken until the end of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Con 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Delay Damage"}]},"shortSummary":"Once per encounter, you may delay the effects of damage taken until the end of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id":"50903195fbb5d090","name":"Blaster Barrage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make an attack with a weapon set on Autofire that deals damage to at least one target within the designated area, you grant a +2 circumstance bonus on any of your allies' Autofire attacks made against that same target until the beginning of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Coordinated Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":33,"tags":["ally_support","area_pressure","autofire","feat","general","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Blaster_Barrage</p>\n<p>You and your allies engulf an area with dense blaster fire.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Coordinated Attack</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you make an attack with a weapon set on Autofire that deals damage to at least one target within the designated area, you grant a +2 circumstance bonus on any of your allies&#x27; Autofire attacks made against that same target until the beginning of your next turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Blaster Barrage"}]},"shortSummary":"Automatically Aid Another when using Autofire attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Coordinated Attack","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Blaster_Barrage"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.blaster_barrage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Blaster_Barrage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"513f0d9e7eb6965b","name":"Opportunistic Retreat","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever an opponent provokes an Attack of Opportunity from you, once per turn you can sacrifice the attack to move a number of squares equal to one-half your Speed. Moving in this way does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"Combat Reflexes","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","mobility","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Retreat</p>\n<p>When your opponent lets down his guard, you can better position yourself to press your advantage.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Combat Reflexes</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Whenever an opponent provokes an Attack of Opportunity from you, once per turn you can sacrifice the attack to move a number of squares equal to one-half your Speed. Moving in this way does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Opportunistic Retreat"}]},"shortSummary":"Sacrifice Attack of Opportunity to move at half speed.","prerequisitesText":"Combat Reflexes","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Retreat"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.opportunistic_retreat","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Retreat","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"51a2fdd9a7965111","name":"Stand Tall","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter when you take damage, all allies who are within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight can, as a Reaction, make a single attack on the target that damaged you.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":26,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stand_Tall</p>\n<p>Your courage under fire inspires those around you to acts of bravery.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Once per encounter when you take damage, all allies who are within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight can, as a Reaction, make a single attack on the target that damaged you.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Stand Tall"}]},"shortSummary":"When you take damage, nearby allies attack your attacker.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stand_Tall"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.stand_tall","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stand_Tall","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"526109c14cc81285","name":"Sith Military Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, as a Reaction when you reduce a target to 0 Hit Points or deal damage that exceeds the target's Damage Threshold, you can activate this Feat to cause all enemies within 6 squares of that target to take a -2 penalty to all Defenses until the end of your next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":29,"tags":["background_opportunity","faction_training","feat","general","military","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sith_Military_Training</p>\n<p>You are trained in Sith military fighting techniques, giving you an advantage in melee combat. This training is generally given to rank and file military members of The Sith Empire regardless of their Force training.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Once per encounter, as a Reaction when you reduce a target to 0 Hit Points or deal damage that exceeds the target&#x27;s Damage Threshold, you can activate this Feat to cause all enemies within 6 squares of that target to take a -2 penalty to all Defenses until the end of your next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Sith Military Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Upon debilitating an opponent, you can cause other opponents to lose heart.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sith_Military_Training"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.sith_military_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sith_Military_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"52f1a7f7eb33a1f4","name":"Attack Combo (Fire and Strike)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you hit a single target with two consecutive ranged, melee, and/or Unarmed attacks during the same turn, any additional ranged, melee, or Unarmed attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.","prerequisite":"Attack Combo (Melee), Attack Combo (Ranged), Base Attack Bonus +9","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":15,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Fire_and_Strike)</p>\n<p>You can make deadly ranged and melee attacks in rapid succession.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Attack Combo (Melee), Attack Combo (Ranged), Base Attack Bonus +9</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you hit a single target with two consecutive ranged, melee, and/or Unarmed attacks during the same turn, any additional ranged, melee, or Unarmed attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":9}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Attack Combo (Fire and Strike)"}]},"shortSummary":"Deal +1 die of damage on Unarmed, melee, or ranged attacks until the end of your next turn after hitting an enemy with two Unarmed, melee, or ranged attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Attack Combo (Melee), Attack Combo (Ranged), Base Attack Bonus +9","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Fire_and_Strike)"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.attack_combo_fire_and_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Fire_and_Strike)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"53444cc061d81627","name":"Force Boon","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You gain three additional Force Points at each level.","prerequisite":"Force Sensitivity","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":94,"tags":["feat","force","force_point_spend","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Boon</p>\n<p>You are able to draw upon The Force more often than less skilled users.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Sensitivity</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You gain three additional Force Points at each level.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RESOURCE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Force Boon"}],"resourceRules":{"forcePoints":[{"type":"MAX_BONUS","value":3,"description":"Gain three additional Force Points at each level."}]}},"shortSummary":"Gain three additional Force Points at each level.","prerequisitesText":"Force Sensitivity","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Boon"},"effects":[{"_id":"77311d06-cd4c-4e4e-88a1-3eb53ba7bf60","name":"Force Boon","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Force Boon","effectType":"passive","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.force_boon","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Boon","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"53f600d68f3afdc3","name":"Unwavering Resolve","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 insight bonus to Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks.","prerequisite":"Trained in Perception","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["defense","feat","general","skill_deception","skill_persuasion","skill_synergy","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unwavering_Resolve</p>\n<p>You are not easily swayed by the words of others, and can see through deceptions thanks to your keen mind.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Perception</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You gain a +5 insight bonus to Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"43c5941072ec78af"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Unwavering Resolve"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a +5 bonus to Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Perception","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unwavering_Resolve"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.unwavering_resolve","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unwavering_Resolve","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"54d6201340a6757f","name":"Headstrong","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Will Defense against fear effects and may reroll a failed Will Defense check once per encounter.","prerequisite":"","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":25,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.will","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Headstrong"}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Will Defense against fear effects and may reroll a failed Will Defense check once per encounter."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will","turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id":"5535b5d495f381f5","name":"Recurring Success","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you select this Feat, choose one Talent or Feat that can normally be used once per encounter. You can use that Talent or Feat one additional time per encounter.","prerequisite":"None","special":"You can select this Feat multiple times. Each time you do so, you must choose a different Talent or Feat to gain the benefits of this Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":23,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recurring_Success</p>\n<p>You know how to make your enemies fall for the same trick twice.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you select this Feat, choose one Talent or Feat that can normally be used once per encounter. You can use that Talent or Feat one additional time per encounter.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can select this Feat multiple times. Each time you do so, you must choose a different Talent or Feat to gain the benefits of this Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Recurring Success"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain extra use of a 1/encounter Talent or Feat.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recurring_Success"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.recurring_success","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recurring_Success","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"55483fd350b3ba28","name":"Aquatic Specialists","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Swim checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Swim","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_swim","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain bonuses on Swim checks when near allies."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"conditional_skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Aquatic Specialists: +3 bonus to swim checks when the near-allies condition is confirmed.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"aquatic-specialists","skillKeys":["swim"],"value":3,"type":"untyped","requiresContextFlags":["nearAllies"],"description":"Aquatic Specialists: +3 when near supporting allies."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Swim checks when near allies."},"effects":[{"_id":"457bea9c-bde5-4d8e-b463-622d2db80636","name":"Aquatic Specialists","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Aquatic Specialists","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.aquatic_specialists"}}}
{"_id":"56367f3943ee8c17","name":"Sniper","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You always ignore Soft Cover (that is, Cover provided by a character, creature, or Droid) when you make a ranged attack.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"","normalText":"You can only ignore Cover if you Aim before making a ranged attack.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["accuracy","cover_play","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged","setup","sniping"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper</p>\n<p>You are particularly adept at hitting the right target in a crowd.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You always ignore Soft Cover (that is, Cover provided by a character, creature, or Droid) when you make a ranged attack.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>You can only ignore Cover if you Aim before making a ranged attack.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Sniper"}]},"shortSummary":"You ignore Soft Cover when making a ranged attack.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.sniper","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5824e2360feb505a","name":"Improved Grapple","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 bonus on grapple checks and do not provoke attacks of opportunity when initiating a grapple.","prerequisite":"Int 13, Grapple","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Improved Grapple"}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +5 bonus on grapple checks and do not provoke attacks of opportunity when initiating a grapple."},"effects":[{"_id":"051a0e7f-c11a-44af-95eb-683f9d8d7467","name":"Improved Grapple","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Improved Grapple","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Improved Grapple"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"58d3d0aece0f3bdc","name":"Improved Sleight of Hand","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Sleight of Hand application of the Stealth Skill, you can use your Deception Skill to improve your chances of success. Prior to making the Stealth check, you can make a Deception check as a Swift Action. The opposed Perception check of anyone attempting to notice your action must exceed both your Deception check and your Stealth check.\n\nAdditionally, you can, as a single Action, use Improved Sleight of Hand to simultaneously draw and palm a weapon two sizes smaller than you. Make a Stealth check as a Free Action when drawing your weapon to successfully conceal it in a position in your hand (Or similar appendage), where you can use it on a following Action. Once the weapon is used, you can attempt to palm it again as a Swift Action.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 15, Skill Focus (Deception), Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":23,"tags":["feat","general","skill_deception","skill_sleight_of_hand","skill_stealth","skill_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Sleight_of_Hand</p>\n<p>You manipulate small objects quickly, and they seemingly disappear with a flick of your wrist. You excel at hiding objects when observed, even at close range.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 15, Skill Focus (Deception), Trained in Stealth</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When using the Sleight of Hand application of the Stealth Skill, you can use your Deception Skill to improve your chances of success. Prior to making the Stealth check, you can make a Deception check as a Swift Action. The opposed Perception check of anyone attempting to notice your action must exceed both your Deception check and your Stealth check.</p>\n<p>Additionally, you can, as a single Action, use Improved Sleight of Hand to simultaneously draw and palm a weapon two sizes smaller than you. Make a Stealth check as a Free Action when drawing your weapon to successfully conceal it in a position in your hand (Or similar appendage), where you can use it on a following Action. Once the weapon is used, you can attempt to palm it again as a Swift Action.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Improved Sleight of Hand"}]},"shortSummary":"Use Deception to aid your Stealth check to use Sleight of Hand; use Stealth to draw and palm a weapon simultaneously.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 15, Skill Focus (Deception), Trained in Stealth","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Sleight_of_Hand"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.improved_sleight_of_hand","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Sleight_of_Hand","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"59e495de34a23def","name":"Leader of Droids","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you provide a beneficial, Mind-Affecting effect to your allies, you may select from among these allies a number of Droids equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1). The Droids you designate ignore their Mind-Affecting immunity with regards to this effect, provided they are willing to ignore this immunity.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","social","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Leader_of_Droids</p>\n<p>You are experienced in leading Droids, and you know how to direct them tactically.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Whenever you provide a beneficial, Mind-Affecting effect to your allies, you may select from among these allies a number of Droids equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1). The Droids you designate ignore their Mind-Affecting immunity with regards to this effect, provided they are willing to ignore this immunity.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Leader of Droids"}]},"shortSummary":"Allied Droids benefit from your beneficial Mind-Affecting effects.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Leader_of_Droids"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.leader_of_droids","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Leader_of_Droids","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5a2ba2f28bc5ee01","name":"Perfect Intuition","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Reroll Initiative checks, always keeping the better result.","prerequisite":"Cerean","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["control","feat","grapple","racial","reroll","skill_initiative","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity","skill_reroll","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-cerean"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Reroll Initiative checks, always keeping the better result."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"skill_reroll_phase8","description":"Perfect Intuition: reroll Initiative checks and keep the better result.","skillRerolls":[{"id":"perfect-intuition","skillKeys":["initiative"],"outcome":"keepBetter","label":"Perfect Intuition","description":"Perfect Intuition: reroll Initiative checks and keep the better result."}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll Initiative checks, always keeping the better result."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.perfect_intuition"}}}
{"_id":"5afd91fb081e576b","name":"Linguist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a number of additional Languages equal to 1 + your Intelligence modifier (Minimum 1).","prerequisite":"Intelligence 13","special":"You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you gain a number of additional languages equal to 1 + your Intelligence modifier (Minimum 1). If your Intelligence modifier increases so does the number of languages granted by this Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["ability_intelligence","feat","general","choice_required","grant_choice","deferred_choice","choice_source_grant_pool"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Linguist</p>\n<p>You pick up languages quickly and easily.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You gain a number of additional Languages equal to 1 + your Intelligence modifier (Minimum 1).</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you gain a number of additional languages equal to 1 + your Intelligence modifier (Minimum 1). If your Intelligence modifier increases so does the number of languages granted by this Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"int","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Linguist"}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"grant_entitlement","required":true,"status":"deferred_grant_step_not_immediate_choice","choiceKind":"language_pick","storagePath":"flags.swse.pendingEntitlements.language_pick","choiceSource":"grantPool","grantType":"language","grantRegistry":"language","countFormula":"max(1, 1 + intelligenceModifier)","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.language_pick","ability":"int","minimum":1,"dynamic":true,"repeatable":true},"shortSummary":"Gain bonus Languages equal to 1 + your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1).","prerequisitesText":"Intelligence 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Linguist"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.linguist","requiresImmediateChoice":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Linguist","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5ba03b04f0f1c7d7","name":"Recovering Surge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you catch a Second Wind, you move +1 step on the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":22,"tags":["condition_track","cover_play","defense","feat","general","recovery","second_wind","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recovering_Surge</p>\n<p>When you get back into the fight, you do not let your wounds hamper you.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you catch a Second Wind, you move +1 step on the Condition Track.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Recovering Surge"}],"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"CONDITION_RECOVERY_ON_USE","steps":1,"description":"Move +1 step on the Condition Track when you catch a Second Wind."}]}},"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"CONDITION_RECOVERY_ON_USE","steps":1}]},"shortSummary":"Move up the Condition Track when you catch a Second Wind.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recovering_Surge"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.recovering_surge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recovering_Surge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5bedd71f0eead6b9","name":"Martial Arts II","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Damage dealt by your Unarmed attacks increases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense (Which stacks with the dodge bonus granted by the Martial Arts I Feat).","prerequisite":"Martial Arts I, Base Attack Bonus +3.","special":"A situation that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense (If any) also makes you lose any dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.","normalText":"The amount of damage you deal with a successful Unarmed attack is based on your size: Small, 1d3; Medium, 1d4; Large, 1d6.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed","unarmed_damage_step","unarmed_damage_scaling"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_II</p>\n<p>You are a master at fighting Unarmed.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Martial Arts I, Base Attack Bonus +3.</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Damage dealt by your Unarmed attacks increases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense (Which stacks with the dodge bonus granted by the Martial Arts I Feat).</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>The amount of damage you deal with a successful Unarmed attack is based on your size: Small, 1d3; Medium, 1d4; Large, 1d6.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>A situation that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense (If any) also makes you lose any dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":3}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","value":1,"type":"dodge","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Martial Arts II: +1 dodge bonus to Reflex Defense"}],"rules":[{"type":"UNARMED_DAMAGE_STEP","params":{"steps":1},"description":"Martial Arts II: increase unarmed attack damage by one die step"}]},"shortSummary":"Increases damage from Unarmed attacks by one die step; gain +1 bonus to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Martial Arts I, Base Attack Bonus +3.","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_II"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"id":"swse.feat.martial_arts_ii","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_II","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5bef5e65e532ba7c","name":"Wicked Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you damage a target with a single, non- Area Attack using the Rapid Strike Feat, once per turn on your turn, you can immediately make a second attack at a -2 penalty against a second target within your reach. If this attack hits, you deal half of the original attack's damage to that target.","prerequisite":"Rapid Strike","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":30,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wicked_Strike</p>\n<p>Your melee attacks can catch bystanders.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rapid Strike</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you damage a target with a single, non- Area Attack using the Rapid Strike Feat, once per turn on your turn, you can immediately make a second attack at a -2 penalty against a second target within your reach. If this attack hits, you deal half of the original attack&#x27;s damage to that target.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Wicked Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain extra attack on a second target upon damaging the first target.","prerequisitesText":"Rapid Strike","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wicked_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.wicked_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wicked_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5cc1216874c79087","name":"Educated","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose two Knowledge skills. You gain a +5 bonus on checks with those skills.","prerequisite":"","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","knowledge","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"skill.knowledge_galactichistory","type":"untyped","value":5,"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Migrated from AE system.skills.knowledge_galactichistory.miscMod"},{"target":"skill.knowledge_socialsciences","type":"untyped","value":5,"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Migrated from AE system.skills.knowledge_socialsciences.miscMod"}]},"shortSummary":"Choose two Knowledge skills."},"effects":[{"name":"Educated","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.skills.knowledge_galactichistory.miscMod","mode":2,"value":"5","priority":20}],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"skill-bonus","skill":"knowledgegalactichistory","source":"Educated","migratedToPassive":true}}},{"name":"Educated","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.skills.knowledge_socialsciences.miscMod","mode":2,"value":"5","priority":20}],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"skill-bonus","skill":"knowledgesocialsciences","source":"Educated","migratedToPassive":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5d17898fc9652370","name":"Droid Hunter","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While wielding a weapon with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls against Droid enemies, or +4 if you are using a weapon that deals Ion Damage.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["feat","general","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Hunter</p>\n<p>You have learned to target the delicate parts of your Droid opponents, taking advantage of their mechanical frailties.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>While wielding a weapon with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls against Droid enemies, or +4 if you are using a weapon that deals Ion Damage.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Droid Hunter"}]},"shortSummary":"Deal +2 damage to Droid enemies, or +4 when using an Ion Weapon.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Hunter"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.droid_hunter","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Hunter","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5e1e84d933295217","name":"Experienced Medic","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can perform Surgery on a number of creatures equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 2) simultaneously. You make Treat Injury checks for each individual creature as normal.","prerequisite":"Trained in Treat Injury","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":22,"tags":["feat","general","healing","skill_treat_injury","support"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Experienced_Medic</p>\n<p>You have spent so much time on the battlefield that patching up wounded allies has become second nature to you.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Treat Injury</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can perform Surgery on a number of creatures equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 2) simultaneously. You make Treat Injury checks for each individual creature as normal.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"treatinjury"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Experienced Medic"}]},"shortSummary":"Perform Surgery on multiple creatures simultaneously.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Treat Injury","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Experienced_Medic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.experienced_medic","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Experienced_Medic","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5e471161ad85b040","name":"Vehicular Surge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If the Vehicle you Pilot is Colossal or smaller and is reduced to fewer than one-half its maximum Hit Points, once per day as a Swift Action your Vehicle gains a number of Bonus Hit Points equal to one-quarter its maximum Hit Point total. Damage is subtracted from Bonus Hit Points first, and any Bonus Hit Points remaining at the end of the encounter are lost. Bonus Hit Points do not stack.","prerequisite":"Trained in Pilot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":23,"tags":["defense","durability","feat","general","hit_points","skill_pilot","skill_synergy","survivability","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Surge</p>\n<p>You can coax more out of Vehicles than other pilots can, staying in the fight when others might be destroyed.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Pilot</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If the Vehicle you Pilot is Colossal or smaller and is reduced to fewer than one-half its maximum Hit Points, once per day as a Swift Action your Vehicle gains a number of Bonus Hit Points equal to one-quarter its maximum Hit Point total. Damage is subtracted from Bonus Hit Points first, and any Bonus Hit Points remaining at the end of the encounter are lost. Bonus Hit Points do not stack.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"b8dad0c963f046c6"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Vehicular Surge"}]},"shortSummary":"Once per day, gain Bonus Hit Points for a Vehicle you Pilot.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Pilot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Surge"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.vehicular_surge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Surge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5f479944307731d1","name":"Attack Combo (Melee)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you hit a single target with two consecutive melee and/or Unarmed attacks during the same turn, any additional melee or Unarmed attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +3","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":15,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Melee)</p>\n<p>After landing successive blows against a single target, your melee and Unarmed attacks become more devastating.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +3</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you hit a single target with two consecutive melee and/or Unarmed attacks during the same turn, any additional melee or Unarmed attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":3}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Attack Combo (Melee)"}]},"shortSummary":"Deal +1 die of damage on Unarmed or melee attacks until the end of your next turn after hitting an enemy with two Unarmed or melee attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +3","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Melee)"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.attack_combo_melee","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Melee)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"600f43af4edb16f7","name":"Whirlwind Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Full-Round Action, you can make an Area Attack with your melee weapon, striking every target within your reach. This Whirlwind Attack uses the Area Attack rules; you make one attack roll and apply the result to every target in range.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13, Intelligence 13, Melee Defense, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["crowd_control","feat","full_round_action","general","multi_target","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Whirlwind_Attack</p>\n<p>You can strike nearby opponents in an amazing, spinning melee attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 13, Intelligence 13, Melee Defense, Base Attack Bonus +4</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>As a Full-Round Action, you can make an Area Attack with your melee weapon, striking every target within your reach. This Whirlwind Attack uses the Area Attack rules; you make one attack roll and apply the result to every target in range.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13},{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Whirlwind Attack"}]},"shortSummary":"Make one melee attack against each opponent within reach.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13, Intelligence 13, Melee Defense, Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Whirlwind_Attack"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.whirlwind_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Whirlwind_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6179746c48e30c26","name":"Nikto Survival","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Select a Nikto subspecies: Kajain'sa'Nikto (Desert), Kadas'sa'Nikto (Forest), Esral'sa'Nikto (Mountains), Gluss'sa'Nikto (Ocean), M'shento'su,Nikto (Arctic). In addition to the usual Nikto Species Traits, when operating in an environment advantageous to your native subspecies, you can reroll any Survival check, taking the better result.","prerequisite":"Nikto","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":26,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase10","feat","general","reroll","skill_survival","skill_synergy","species_prerequisite_phase10","species_rule"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nikto_Survival</p>\n<p>You gain an additional boost to your Survival checks, based on your Nikto subspecies.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Nikto</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Select a Nikto subspecies: Kajain&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Desert), Kadas&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Forest), Esral&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Mountains), Gluss&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Ocean), M&#x27;shento&#x27;su,Nikto (Arctic). In addition to the usual Nikto Species Traits, when operating in an environment advantageous to your native subspecies, you can reroll any Survival check, taking the better result.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"species_rule_phase10_skill_reroll_hook","description":"Nikto Survival: reroll Survival checks in native environment. Context must explicitly indicate native environment.","skillRerolls":[{"id":"nikto-survival","skillKeys":["survival"],"requiresContextFlags":["nativeEnvironment"],"outcome":"keepSecond","label":"Nikto Survival","description":"Reroll Survival checks in native environment; GM/context determines native environment."}],"conditionNotes":[{"id":"nikto-survival","label":"Nikto Survival","severity":"info","text":"May reroll Survival checks in native environment when the GM/context confirms it.","mechanical":true,"gmEnforced":true}]},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"species","species":["Nikto"]}],"_source":"phase10_species_prereq"},"shortSummary":"Reroll Survival checks in native environment.","prerequisitesText":"Nikto","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nikto_Survival"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.nikto_survival","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nikto_Survival","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"61c053191d05d0a2","name":"Knife Trick","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you have a concealed weapon, you Threaten squares as though armed with a melee weapon. When you can make an Attack of Opportunity, you can draw a weapon you have successfully concealed on your person and make a single attack against the target.\n\nIf you choose not to draw your concealed weapon and attack with it, you cannot make the Attack of Opportunity unless you would otherwise normally be able to do so.","prerequisite":"Lightning Draw, Quick Draw, Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"With the Quick Draw feat, drawing or holstering a weapon is a Swift Action.","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knife_Trick</p>\n<p>You can use a concealed weapon to deadly effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Lightning Draw, Quick Draw, Trained in Stealth</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you have a concealed weapon, you Threaten squares as though armed with a melee weapon. When you can make an Attack of Opportunity, you can draw a weapon you have successfully concealed on your person and make a single attack against the target.</p>\n<p>If you choose not to draw your concealed weapon and attack with it, you cannot make the Attack of Opportunity unless you would otherwise normally be able to do so.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>With the Quick Draw feat, drawing or holstering a weapon is a Swift Action.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"6d2ac22d9fcf402f"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Knife Trick"}]},"shortSummary":"Attack of Opportunity with concealed weapon to greater effect.","prerequisitesText":"Lightning Draw, Quick Draw, Trained in Stealth","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knife_Trick"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.knife_trick","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knife_Trick","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"627b92fefdc552d2","name":"Forceful Recovery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"Whenever you catch a Second Wind, choose one expended Force Power and return that power to your Force Power Suite.","prerequisite":"Force Sensitivity, Force Training","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["cover_play","defense","feat","force","force_powers","recovery","second_wind","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Recovery</p>\n<p>The Force is strong with you, and it gives you focus and vitality.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Sensitivity, Force Training</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Whenever you catch a Second Wind, choose one expended Force Power and return that power to your Force Power Suite.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Forceful Recovery"}],"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"REGAIN_FORCE_POWER_ON_USE","count":1,"description":"Regain one expended Force power when you catch a Second Wind."}]}},"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"REGAIN_FORCE_POWER_ON_USE"}]},"shortSummary":"Regain one Force Power when you catch a Second Wind.","prerequisitesText":"Force Sensitivity, Force Training","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Recovery"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.forceful_recovery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Recovery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"62fdf44c56b24507","name":"Careful Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you Aim before making a ranged attack, you gain a +1 bonus on your attack roll.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot Feat, Base Attack Bonus +2","special":"A Pilot can use this Feat, but since they must spend at least one Move Action operating their Vehicles, they must split their Aim (two Swift Actions) and attack (Standard Action) into two separate turns, making it more likely that the target will break line of sight or avoid you.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Careful_Shot</p>\n<p>You are particularly skilled at Aiming your attacks.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot Feat, Base Attack Bonus +2</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you Aim before making a ranged attack, you gain a +1 bonus on your attack roll.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>A Pilot can use this Feat, but since they must spend at least one Move Action operating their Vehicles, they must split their Aim (two Swift Actions) and attack (Standard Action) into two separate turns, making it more likely that the target will break line of sight or avoid you.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":2}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Careful Shot: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"carefulShot","label":"Careful Shot","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAim":true,"attackModifier":1,"summary":"When aiming with a ranged weapon, gain +1 on the attack roll."}]},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"If you Aim, gain +1 bonus on the attack roll.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot Feat, Base Attack Bonus +2","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Careful_Shot"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.careful_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Careful_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6335692284f98ec6","name":"Flood of Fire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make an Area Attack with a weapon set on Autofire, and you are proficient with that weapon, all targets in the area lose all dodge or deflection bonuses to Reflex Defense against the Autofire attack.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":23,"tags":["area_pressure","autofire","feat","general","multi_target","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flood_of_Fire</p>\n<p>You fill the air with weapon fire, keeping your opponents from escaping the barrage.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you make an Area Attack with a weapon set on Autofire, and you are proficient with that weapon, all targets in the area lose all dodge or deflection bonuses to Reflex Defense against the Autofire attack.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Flood of Fire"}]},"shortSummary":"Ignore enemies' dodge and deflection bonus to Reflex Defense when making Area Attacks with a weapon set on Autofire.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flood_of_Fire"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.flood_of_fire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flood_of_Fire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6342effd242f0b61","name":"Turn and Burn","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Withdraw Action, you can move up to 2 squares to escape Threatened squares without provoking an Attack of Opportunity, and you can move your Speed. You can spend a Force Point as a Reaction to an enemy ending its movement adjacent to you to Withdraw.","prerequisite":"Droid; Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion; Dexterity 13","special":"You must be equipped with Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion to use this Feat.","normalText":"When using the Withdraw Action, you can normally move only 1 square to escape a Threatened square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity and can move only up to half your Speed.","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":26,"tags":["feat","force_point_spend","general","mobility","reaction","resource_spend","skill_pilot","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger&#x27;s Guide to Droids</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Turn_and_Burn</p>\n<p>You can retreat from enemies with additional speed and agility.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid; Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion; Dexterity 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When using the Withdraw Action, you can move up to 2 squares to escape Threatened squares without provoking an Attack of Opportunity, and you can move your Speed. You can spend a Force Point as a Reaction to an enemy ending its movement adjacent to you to Withdraw.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>When using the Withdraw Action, you can normally move only 1 square to escape a Threatened square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity and can move only up to half your Speed.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You must be equipped with Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion to use this Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Turn and Burn"}]},"shortSummary":"Withdraw by clearing threatened squares in up to 2 squares of movement, move your Speed when using the Withdraw Action. Withdraw as a Reaction by spending a Force Point.","prerequisitesText":"Droid; Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion; Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Turn_and_Burn"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.turn_and_burn","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Turn_and_Burn","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6356fd5ea46b9c6c","name":"Impulsive Flight","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can Withdraw one extra square using the Withdraw Action.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":25,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impulsive_Flight</p>\n<p>You are not above running when the situation turns against you.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can Withdraw one extra square using the Withdraw Action.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Impulsive Flight"}]},"shortSummary":"Withdraw faster.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impulsive_Flight"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.impulsive_flight","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impulsive_Flight","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"63dbb0e9623f7fce","name":"Resolute Stance","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you Fight Defensively, you gain a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense. If you make no attacks until your next turn, you gain a +5 morale bonus to your Will Defense until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"When you Fight Defensively you only get a dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense.","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":23,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resolute_Stance</p>\n<p>By standing your ground, you focus your mind to repel any assault.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +1</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you Fight Defensively, you gain a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense. If you make no attacks until your next turn, you gain a +5 morale bonus to your Will Defense until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>When you Fight Defensively you only get a dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Resolute Stance"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain +2 or +5 to Will Defense when you Fight Defensively.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resolute_Stance"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.resolute_stance","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resolute_Stance","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"643c54c206ed5f64","name":"Swarm","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +1 circumstance bonus on melee attack rolls for each allied character adjacent to your target.","prerequisite":"Coordinated Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":37,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Swarm</p>\n<p>You are trained to fight with allies en masse.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Coordinated Attack</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You gain a +1 circumstance bonus on melee attack rolls for each allied character adjacent to your target.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Swarm"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain +1 bonus on melee attack rolls when allies are adjacent.","prerequisitesText":"Coordinated Attack","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Swarm"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.swarm","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Swarm","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"647d77a8f5ab9af3","name":"Keen Force Mind","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate mind-affecting Force powers.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Jedi Academy Training Manual","page":31,"tags":["feat","force"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Keen Force Mind"}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate mind-affecting Force powers."},"effects":[{"_id":"53d22820-a807-4a74-bcc8-77674689b0fb","name":"Keen Force Mind","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Keen Force Mind","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Keen Force Mind"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"648a4f16669056f0","name":"Triple Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group. When you use the Full Attack Action, you may make one additional attack when wielding such a Weapon. However, you take a -5 penalty on all attack rolls until your next turn because you're trading precision for speed. The extra attack and penalty stack with those of Double Attack.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +11, Double Attack (Chosen Weapon)","special":"You may select this Feat multiple times. Each time you select this Feat, it applies to a different Exotic Weapon or weapon group.","normalText":"Making a single attack is a Standard Action.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Attack</p>\n<p>You can make an additional attack during a round of combat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +11, Double Attack (Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group. When you use the Full Attack Action, you may make one additional attack when wielding such a Weapon. However, you take a -5 penalty on all attack rolls until your next turn because you&#x27;re trading precision for speed. The extra attack and penalty stack with those of Double Attack.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>Making a single attack is a Standard Action.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You may select this Feat multiple times. Each time you select this Feat, it applies to a different Exotic Weapon or weapon group.</p>\n<h4>Additional Triple Attack Effects</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you take this feat with Heavy Weapons, it works normally with Vehicle Weapons.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":9}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Triple Attack"}]},"shortSummary":"Make second extra attack with chosen weapon during Full Attack, additional -5 penalty to all attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +11, Double Attack (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Attack"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.triple_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6557f371e55b900a","name":"Distracting Droid","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Standard Action, make a Persuasion check against the Will Defense of all enemies that are within 6 squares of you and that can see or hear you, as determined by the Gamemaster. If the check equals or exceeds an enemy's Will Defense, the enemy loses one Move Action on its next turn. If the attack exceeds an enemy's Will Defense by 10 or more, the enemy is also Flat-Footed until the start of your next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.","prerequisite":"Droid","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":19,"tags":["action_economy","feat","general","move_action","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger&#x27;s Guide to Droids</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Distracting_Droid</p>\n<p>You use lights, holographic projectors, sudden movements, erratic flight, odd noises, or other uniquely Droid techniques to distract an enemy.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>As a Standard Action, make a Persuasion check against the Will Defense of all enemies that are within 6 squares of you and that can see or hear you, as determined by the Gamemaster. If the check equals or exceeds an enemy&#x27;s Will Defense, the enemy loses one Move Action on its next turn. If the attack exceeds an enemy&#x27;s Will Defense by 10 or more, the enemy is also Flat-Footed until the start of your next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Distracting Droid"}]},"shortSummary":"Attempt to deny enemies within 6 squares their next Move Action, with a chance to make enemies Flat-Footed.","prerequisitesText":"Droid","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Distracting_Droid"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.distracting_droid","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Distracting_Droid","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6673cd53493a9d6c","name":"Forceful Slam","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate Force Slam.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force, Force Slam","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["feat","force","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Forceful Slam"}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate Force Slam."},"effects":[{"_id":"dd3bb5b5-ed2f-4950-9cb1-faca1dce72c0","name":"Forceful Slam","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Forceful Slam","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Forceful Slam"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"6723270208549f73","name":"Mandalorian Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Charging Fire Feat, you gain a +2 bonus to a ranged attack made at the end of a Charge. As with a normal Charge, you still take a -2 penalty to your Reflex Defense, but you also gain a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense until the beginning of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Charging Fire","special":"","normalText":"You gain no bonus to a ranged attack make at the end of a Charge with the Charging Fire Feat.","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mandalorian_Training</p>\n<p>You are trained in Mandalorian fighting techniques, giving you an advantage in many types of combat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charging Fire</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When using the Charging Fire Feat, you gain a +2 bonus to a ranged attack made at the end of a Charge. As with a normal Charge, you still take a -2 penalty to your Reflex Defense, but you also gain a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense until the beginning of your next turn.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>You gain no bonus to a ranged attack make at the end of a Charge with the Charging Fire Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Mandalorian Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls when using the Charging Fire feat.","prerequisitesText":"Charging Fire","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mandalorian_Training"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.mandalorian_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mandalorian_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"691b3a9309b28e60","name":"Demoralizing Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you successfully deal damage to an opponent with an Attack of Opportunity, you can immediately make a Persuasion check to Intimidate the opponent as a Free Action.","prerequisite":"Charisma 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":17,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense","offense_melee","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Demoralizing_Strike</p>\n<p>You know how to dishearten your opponents when they least expect it.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charisma 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you successfully deal damage to an opponent with an Attack of Opportunity, you can immediately make a Persuasion check to Intimidate the opponent as a Free Action.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Demoralizing Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"Make an Intimidation check when you deal damage with an Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisitesText":"Charisma 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Demoralizing_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.demoralizing_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Demoralizing_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6b6a0dc594ad4e3c","name":"Tae-Jitsu Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"Deal more damage on critical hits. Use Dodge against enemies.","prerequisite":"Dodge, Martial Arts I, Trained in Initiative","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","feat_chain","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Deal more damage on critical hits. Use Dodge against enemies."},"martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Tae-Jitsu Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Deal more damage on critical hits."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.tae_jitsu_training"}}}
{"_id":"6ba02f4dd4c3bfe5","name":"Elder's Knowledge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you can substitute a Knowledge (Galactic Lore) or Knowledge (Social Sciences) check for a Wisdom or Wisdom -related check.","prerequisite":"Skill Focus (Knowledge (Galactic Lore)) or Skill Focus (Knowledge (Social Sciences))","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":20,"tags":["ability_wisdom","feat","general","knowledge","skill_knowledge","skill_synergy","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Elder&#x27;s_Knowledge</p>\n<p>You have gained the wisdom of elders, whether through your own experiences or by learning from their instruction.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Skill Focus (Knowledge (Galactic Lore)) or Skill Focus (Knowledge (Social Sciences))</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Once per encounter, you can substitute a Knowledge (Galactic Lore) or Knowledge (Social Sciences) check for a Wisdom or Wisdom -related check.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Elder's Knowledge"}]},"shortSummary":"Substitute a Knowledge (Social Sciences) or Knowledge (Galactic Lore) skill check for a Wisdom -related Skill Check.","prerequisitesText":"Skill Focus (Knowledge (Galactic Lore)) or Skill Focus (Knowledge (Social Sciences))","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Elder's_Knowledge"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.elders_knowledge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Elder's_Knowledge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6cf1898b8c3c837c","name":"Scavenger","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can spend 1 hour scavenging materials from other Vehicles or objects. When you do so, you make a Perception check to determine the value of the parts scavenged. You produce raw materials equal in value to the result of your Perception check x 30 credits. You must apply these raw materials toward the cost of construction of a single object (see Build Object), and you can scavenge parts for only a single object at any given time. Additionally, you can scavenge raw materials only once for any given object you are attempting to build.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","knowledge","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":["21dfe84d159a1b7f","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Scavenger</p>\n<p>You are adept at digging through broken objects and junk piles to come up with the raw material needed for certain tasks.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can spend 1 hour scavenging materials from other Vehicles or objects. When you do so, you make a Perception check to determine the value of the parts scavenged. You produce raw materials equal in value to the result of your Perception check x 30 credits. You must apply these raw materials toward the cost of construction of a single object (see Build Object), and you can scavenge parts for only a single object at any given time. Additionally, you can scavenge raw materials only once for any given object you are attempting to build.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Scavenger"}]},"shortSummary":"Gather materials for building objects","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Scavenger"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.scavenger","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Scavenger","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6d8ce2807c579289","name":"Trustworthy","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Persuasion checks and may reroll a failed Persuasion check once per encounter.","prerequisite":"","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"skill","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Trustworthy"}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Persuasion checks and may reroll a failed Persuasion check once per encounter."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id":"6dcb59b199dba6a1","name":"Hijkata Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"Make counterattacks. Impose penalties to enemy attacks.","prerequisite":"Combat Reflexes, Martial Arts I","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","feat_chain","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Make counterattacks. Impose penalties to enemy attacks."},"martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":1,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee","proximity.ally-nearby","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Hijkata Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Make counterattacks."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee","proximity.ally-nearby","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.hijkata_training"}}}
{"_id":"6e3b0ca6413e607c","name":"Crossfire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you miss when making a ranged attack against a target that has Soft Cover (that is, Cover provided by another character, creature, or Droid), you can immediately make an attack roll (with the same weapon and at the same attack bonus) against the target that is providing the Soft Cover. You can only use this Feat once per round.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":33,"tags":["cover_play","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crossfire</p>\n<p>You are skilled at aiming your shots so that they have a chance of hitting more than one target.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you miss when making a ranged attack against a target that has Soft Cover (that is, Cover provided by another character, creature, or Droid), you can immediately make an attack roll (with the same weapon and at the same attack bonus) against the target that is providing the Soft Cover. You can only use this Feat once per round.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":6}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Crossfire"}]},"shortSummary":"Redirect missed attacks against Soft Cover.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crossfire"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.crossfire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crossfire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6e47c132fbedde08","name":"Deadeye","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you Aim before making a ranged attack and the attack hits, increase the damage you deal by an additional weapon die (3d6 becomes 4d6).","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"The effects of this Feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the Burst Fire or Rapid Shot Feats.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadeye</p>\n<p>You are skilled at picking off enemies with well-Aimed ranged attacks.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you Aim before making a ranged attack and the attack hits, increase the damage you deal by an additional weapon die (3d6 becomes 4d6).</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>The effects of this Feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the Burst Fire or Rapid Shot Feats.</p>\n<h4>Additional Deadeye Effects</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p>A Pilot can use this Feat, but since they must spend at least one Move Action operating their Vehicles, they must split their Aim (two Swift Actions) and attack (Standard Action) into two separate turns, making it more likely that the target will break line of sight or avoid you.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Deadeye: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"deadeye","label":"Deadeye","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAim":true,"damageDiceStepBonus":1,"summary":"When aiming with a ranged weapon, deal +1 die of damage."}]},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"If you Aim, deal extra damage.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadeye"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.deadeye","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadeye","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6ef0920984de0ed0","name":"Risk Taker","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You fall only if you fail a Climb check by 10 or more. Additionally, if you make a Jump check and fail to land on a safe or solid surface (such as if you fall into a pit or fail to clear a stream of lava), you can spend a Force Point as a Free Action and add the result of the Force Point roll to your distance jumped. However, you must land in the first available safe square.","prerequisite":"Trained in Climb or Jump","special":"","normalText":"You fall if you fail a Climb check by 5 or more.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","skill_climb","skill_jump","skill_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Risk_Taker</p>\n<p>You&#x27;re not afraid to make great leaps or climb treacherous slopes, and you know how to put forth the extra effort to make the impossible seem routine.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Climb or Jump</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You fall only if you fail a Climb check by 10 or more. Additionally, if you make a Jump check and fail to land on a safe or solid surface (such as if you fall into a pit or fail to clear a stream of lava), you can spend a Force Point as a Free Action and add the result of the Force Point roll to your distance jumped. However, you must land in the first available safe square.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>You fall if you fail a Climb check by 5 or more.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Risk Taker"}]},"shortSummary":"Improve your chances of success with Climb or Jump checks.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Climb or Jump","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Risk_Taker"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.risk_taker","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Risk_Taker","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6f98dd888bef8d7b","name":"Redirect Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you successfully negate a ranged attack with Deflect, you may redirect the shot to another target within line of sight.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force, Deflect","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":94,"tags":["feat","force","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Redirect Shot"}]},"shortSummary":"When you successfully negate a ranged attack with Deflect, you may redirect the shot to another target within line of sight."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"]}}}
{"_id":"6fb0f56dd9b9b75c","name":"Deadly Sniper","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make a ranged attack against a target that is unaware of you, you gain a +2 bonus on your attack roll and deal +1 die of damage on the first attack each turn.","prerequisite":"Sniper, Trained in Stealth, Base Attack Bonus +9","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":21,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged","sniping"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadly_Sniper</p>\n<p>You are adept at staying out of sight when attacking from hidden positions.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Sniper, Trained in Stealth, Base Attack Bonus +9</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you make a ranged attack against a target that is unaware of you, you gain a +2 bonus on your attack roll and deal +1 die of damage on the first attack each turn.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":9},{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"6d2ac22d9fcf402f"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Deadly Sniper"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain +2 bonus on your ranged attack roll and deal +1 die of damage.","prerequisitesText":"Sniper, Trained in Stealth, Base Attack Bonus +9","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadly_Sniper"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.deadly_sniper","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadly_Sniper","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"70962165bed8e5ed","name":"Gunnery Specialist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While you are the Gunner of a Vehicle, you are considered proficient with Vehicle Weapons. Additionally, once per encounter, you can reroll an attack roll made with a Vehicle Weapon, though you must keep the second result, even if it is worse. You can declare this reroll after you learn the result of the attack roll, but before damage is resolved.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"Taking this Feat satisfies the prerequisites for the Starship Tactics Feat; however, unless you are Trained in Pilot and have the Vehicular Combat Feat, you may only take [Gunner ] Maneuvers when you select Starship Maneuvers for Starship Tactics.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":24,"tags":["feat","general","offense_ranged","reroll","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gunnery_Specialist</p>\n<p>You are right at home in the Gunner&#x27;s seat and use heavy artillery to great effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +1</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>While you are the Gunner of a Vehicle, you are considered proficient with Vehicle Weapons. Additionally, once per encounter, you can reroll an attack roll made with a Vehicle Weapon, though you must keep the second result, even if it is worse. You can declare this reroll after you learn the result of the attack roll, but before damage is resolved.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>Taking this Feat satisfies the prerequisites for the Starship Tactics Feat; however, unless you are Trained in Pilot and have the Vehicular Combat Feat, you may only take [Gunner ] Maneuvers when you select Starship Maneuvers for Starship Tactics.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Gunnery Specialist"}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll an attack made with a Vehicle Weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gunnery_Specialist"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.gunnery_specialist","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gunnery_Specialist","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"70c842436bbb6330","name":"Perfect Swimmer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Reroll Swim checks, always keeping the better result.","prerequisite":"Gungan","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["control","feat","grapple","racial","reroll","skill_swim","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity","skill_reroll","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-gungan"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Reroll Swim checks, always keeping the better result."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"skill_reroll_phase8","description":"Perfect Swimmer: reroll Swim checks and keep the better result.","skillRerolls":[{"id":"perfect-swimmer","skillKeys":["swim"],"outcome":"keepBetter","label":"Perfect Swimmer","description":"Perfect Swimmer: reroll Swim checks and keep the better result."}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll Swim checks, always keeping the better result."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.perfect_swimmer"}}}
{"_id":"70f27646ad28816a","name":"Instinctive Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use a Force Point when making an attack with a weapon with which you are proficient, you can reroll the attack and take the better result. Apply the results of the die from the Force Point to the better result.","prerequisite":"Cannot be a Droid","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":24,"tags":["feat","force_point_spend","general","offense","reroll","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Attack</p>\n<p>Your accuracy improves when you act on instinct. Though you might call it luck, The Force is with you.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Cannot be a Droid</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you use a Force Point when making an attack with a weapon with which you are proficient, you can reroll the attack and take the better result. Apply the results of the die from the Force Point to the better result.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"ACTIVE","subType":"REROLL","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Instinctive Attack"}],"attackRerolls":[{"type":"ATTACK_REROLL","cost":"forcePoint","outcome":"keepBetter","description":"Spend a Force Point to reroll an attack and take the better result."}]},"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"resource":"forcePoint"},"shortSummary":"Spend a Force Point to reroll an attack and take the better result.","prerequisitesText":"Cannot be a Droid","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Attack"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.instinctive_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7146640744fdf052","name":"Combat Reflexes","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When opponents leave themselves open, you may make a number of additional Attacks of Opportunity equal to your Dexterity modifier.\n\nWith this Feat, you may also make Attacks of Opportunity while Flat-Footed. You can still only make one attack for each triggered Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"A character without the Combat Reflexes Feat can make only one Attack of Opportunity per round, and can't make Attacks of Opportunity while Flat-Footed.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":85,"tags":["control","defense","feat","general","opportunity_attack","reaction","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Reflexes</p>\n<p>You can respond quickly and repeatedly to opponents who let their guard down.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When opponents leave themselves open, you may make a number of additional Attacks of Opportunity equal to your Dexterity modifier.</p>\n<p>With this Feat, you may also make Attacks of Opportunity while Flat-Footed. You can still only make one attack for each triggered Attack of Opportunity.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>A character without the Combat Reflexes Feat can make only one Attack of Opportunity per round, and can&#x27;t make Attacks of Opportunity while Flat-Footed.</p>\n<h4>Additional Combat Reflexes Effects</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p>Combined Feat (Return Fire): You may use the Return Fire Feat a number of times during an encounter equal to your Dexterity bonus, but no more than once during a given enemy&#x27;s turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Combat Reflexes"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain additional Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Reflexes"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.combat_reflexes","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Reflexes","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"71892687abbed346","name":"Strong in the Force","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you spend a Force Point to adjust the result of an attack roll, Skill Check, or Ability Check, you roll d8s instead of d6s.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["feat","force","force_point_spend","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_in_the_Force</p>\n<p>You have a particularly strong connection to The Force.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you spend a Force Point to adjust the result of an attack roll, Skill Check, or Ability Check, you roll d8s instead of d6s.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"force.dieSize","value":8,"type":"enhancement","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Strong in the Force: roll d8s instead of d6s when spending a Force Point"}],"resourceRules":{"forcePoints":[{"type":"DIE_SIZE","value":8,"description":"Roll d8s instead of d6s when spending a Force Point."}]}},"shortSummary":"Roll d8s instead of d6s when you spend a Force Point.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_in_the_Force"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.strong_in_the_force","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_in_the_Force","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"72146d8a36d77736","name":"Grand Army of the Republic Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you wear Armor that provides an Equipment bonus to your Fortitude Defense, and you are proficient with that Armor, you also apply the Armor's Equipment bonus to your Will Defense.","prerequisite":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grand_Army_of_the_Republic_Training</p>\n<p>You have received basic training from the Grand Army of the Republic and know how to turn even bulky armor into an asset.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Armor Proficiency (Light)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you wear Armor that provides an Equipment bonus to your Fortitude Defense, and you are proficient with that Armor, you also apply the Armor&#x27;s Equipment bonus to your Will Defense.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Grand Army of the Republic Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Apply your armor's Equipment bonus to your Will Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grand_Army_of_the_Republic_Training"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.grand_army_of_the_republic_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grand_Army_of_the_Republic_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"72183c573d1cc44e","name":"Unhindered Approach","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Jump checks checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Jump","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_jump","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain bonuses on Jump checks checks when near allies."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"conditional_skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Unhindered Approach: +3 bonus to jump checks when the near-allies condition is confirmed.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"unhindered-approach","skillKeys":["jump"],"value":3,"type":"untyped","requiresContextFlags":["nearAllies"],"description":"Unhindered Approach: +3 when near supporting allies."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Jump checks checks when near allies."},"effects":[{"_id":"e235e428-f19c-46cb-baa9-10c7a79edc84","name":"Unhindered Approach","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Unhindered Approach","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.unhindered_approach"}}}
{"_id":"723563f70bd7f28f","name":"Acrobatic Ally","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can hoist or toss an ally of your size or smaller up to 2 squares. You and your ally must act on the same Initiative Count and start in adjacent squares. If you succeed on a DC 20 Acrobatics check as a Standard Action, your ally ends up in a square of your choosing up to 2 squares above or away from you. This counts as a Free Action for your ally and ends your turn. Your ally can then continue his or her turn. If you fail your check, both you and your ally immediately become Prone in your square. Your turn is ended, but your ally can take his or her turn normally.","prerequisite":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Trained in Acrobatics","special":"This Feat can provoke Attacks of Opportunity against either character.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":18,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Ally</p>\n<p>You move an ally around with ease and accuracy by giving him or her a leg up or a helpful toss.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Trained in Acrobatics</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can hoist or toss an ally of your size or smaller up to 2 squares. You and your ally must act on the same Initiative Count and start in adjacent squares. If you succeed on a DC 20 Acrobatics check as a Standard Action, your ally ends up in a square of your choosing up to 2 squares above or away from you. This counts as a Free Action for your ally and ends your turn. Your ally can then continue his or her turn. If you fail your check, both you and your ally immediately become Prone in your square. Your turn is ended, but your ally can take his or her turn normally.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>This Feat can provoke Attacks of Opportunity against either character.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Acrobatic Ally"}]},"shortSummary":"Hoist or toss an ally of your size or smaller up to 2 squares.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Trained in Acrobatics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Ally"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.acrobatic_ally","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Ally","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"74dc095d9ab94915","name":"Returning Bug","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you miss with a Razor Bug or a Thud Bug, the weapon returns to your hand immediately.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":22,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Returning_Bug</p>\n<p>You have mastered the art of using Yuuzhan Vong Thrown Weapons and can cause them to return to your hand.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you miss with a Razor Bug or a Thud Bug, the weapon returns to your hand immediately.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Returning Bug"}]},"shortSummary":"Thrown Razor Bugs and Thud Bugs return to your hand immediately.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Returning_Bug"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.returning_bug","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Returning_Bug","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"752b00692fa5376b","name":"Nimble Team","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Acrobatics checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Acrobatics","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_acrobatics","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain bonuses on Acrobatics checks when near allies."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"conditional_skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Nimble Team: +3 bonus to acrobatics checks when the near-allies condition is confirmed.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"nimble-team","skillKeys":["acrobatics"],"value":3,"type":"untyped","requiresContextFlags":["nearAllies"],"description":"Nimble Team: +3 when near supporting allies."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Acrobatics checks when near allies."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.nimble_team"}}}
{"_id":"75ce7688bdfb0b23","name":"Deceptive Drop","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"During the Surprise Round, if you damage a Flat-Footed target, that target is also knocked Prone if your attack roll also exceeds the target's Fortitude Defense. The target adds its size modifier to its Fortitude Defense:\n\n- Colossal, +50;\n- Gargantuan, +20;\n- Huge, +10;\n- Large, +5;\n- Medium and smaller, +0.","prerequisite":"Trained in Initiative","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":22,"tags":["control","feat","general","knock_prone"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deceptive_Drop</p>\n<p>When you get the drop on opponents, you dazzle them with your speed and ferocity.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Initiative</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>During the Surprise Round, if you damage a Flat-Footed target, that target is also knocked Prone if your attack roll also exceeds the target&#x27;s Fortitude Defense. The target adds its size modifier to its Fortitude Defense:</p>\n<ul><li>Colossal, +50;</li><li>Gargantuan, +20;</li><li>Huge, +10;</li><li>Large, +5;</li><li>Medium and smaller, +0.</li></ul>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"cb5493f65f0bdb62"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["target.is-prone"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Deceptive Drop"}]},"shortSummary":"Flat-Footed targets knocked Prone on Surprise Round.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Initiative","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deceptive_Drop"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["target.is-prone"],"id":"swse.feat.deceptive_drop","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deceptive_Drop","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"75daa55c22ffed5e","name":"Covert Operatives","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Stealth checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","cover_play","defense","feat","skill_stealth","skill_synergy","stealth","survivability","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain bonuses on Stealth checks when near allies."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"conditional_skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Covert Operatives: +3 bonus to stealth checks when the near-allies condition is confirmed.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"covert-operatives","skillKeys":["stealth"],"value":3,"type":"untyped","requiresContextFlags":["nearAllies"],"description":"Covert Operatives: +3 when near supporting allies."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Stealth checks when near allies."},"effects":[{"_id":"acf6131e-f0c7-4851-99dd-0f0efd6241b8","name":"Covert Operatives","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Covert Operatives","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["movement.while-moving","proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.covert_operatives"}}}
{"_id":"75ff82e2dd80091d","name":"Greater Weapon Focus","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls with the selected weapon group. This stacks with Weapon Focus.","prerequisite":"Weapon Focus with selected weapon group, base attack bonus +8","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["accuracy","feat","general","weapon_mastery","choice_required","immediate_choice","weapon_choice","choice_source_prerequisite"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack.bonus","value":1,"type":"untyped","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Greater Weapon Focus: +1 attack with selected Weapon Focus target","predicates":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"]}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"execution_mapped_phase6","choiceKind":"greater_weapon_focus","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.greater_weapon_focus","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.greater_weapon_focus","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","derivesFrom":["weapon_focus"],"consumes":"weapon_focus","provides":"greater_weapon_focus","effectTarget":"attack.bonus","effectValue":1},"shortSummary":"You gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls with the selected weapon group."},"effects":[{"name":"Greater Weapon Focus","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.attackBonus.rifles","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"attack-bonus","weaponGroup":"rifles"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"requiresImmediateChoice":true}}}
{"_id":"765ff8a34e58acac","name":"Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You are proficient with rifles and do not take the -5 penalty when using them.","prerequisite":"","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["build_enabler","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged","weapon_access","weapon_rifle","mapped_phase_1","unlock_grant","choice_variant"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"grants":[{"category":"PROFICIENCY","proficiencyType":"weapon","proficiencies":["rifles"],"description":"Weapon proficiency: rifles"}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"already_resolved_static_variant","required":false,"choiceKind":"weapon_proficiency","value":"rifles","grants":["rifles"]},"shortSummary":"You are proficient with rifles and do not take the -5 penalty when using them."},"effects":[{"_id":"3b695d0d-747b-4081-8b6c-8b5f8584ff43","name":"Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true}}}
{"_id":"773ec00effc7e96f","name":"Armor Proficiency (light)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you wear Light Armor, you take no Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls or Skill Checks. Additionally, you benefit from all of the armor's special Equipment bonuses (if any).","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"A character who wears Light Armor with which they are not proficient takes a -2 Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls as well as Skill Checks made using the following Skills: Acrobatics, Climb, Endurance, Initiative, Jump, Stealth, and Swim. Additionally, the character gains none of the armor's special Equipment bonuses.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":85,"tags":["armor","build_enabler","defense","feat","general","mapped_phase_1","unlock_grant","choice_variant","armor_access"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Light)</p>\n<p>You are proficient with Light Armor, and can wear it without impediment.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you wear Light Armor, you take no Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls or Skill Checks. Additionally, you benefit from all of the armor&#x27;s special Equipment bonuses (if any).</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>A character who wears Light Armor with which they are not proficient takes a -2 Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls as well as Skill Checks made using the following Skills: Acrobatics, Climb, Endurance, Initiative, Jump, Stealth, and Swim. Additionally, the character gains none of the armor&#x27;s special Equipment bonuses.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"grants":[{"category":"PROFICIENCY","proficiencyType":"armor","proficiencies":["light"],"description":"Armor proficiency: light"}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"already_resolved_static_variant","required":false,"choiceKind":"armor_proficiency","value":"light","grants":["light"]},"shortSummary":"No penalty on attacks and no Armor Check Penalty while wearing Light Armor.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Light)"},"effects":[{"_id":"9781a3c7-4e7e-4af0-9dcc-cdea0524b414","name":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.armorProficiency.light","mode":5,"value":"true"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","effectType":"armor_proficiency"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Light)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7767bd8542b4edbd","name":"Frightening Presence","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use Frightful Presence, targets that fail their Will Defense check move -2 steps down the condition track instead of -1.","prerequisite":"Charisma 15, Frightful Presence","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":25,"tags":["control","feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.will","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Frightening Presence"}]},"shortSummary":"When you use Frightful Presence, targets that fail their Will Defense check move -2 steps down the condition track instead of -1."},"effects":[{"name":"Mobile Fighting (vs AoO)","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.defenses.reflex.misc","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":20}],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"feat-conditional-defense","source":"Mobile Fighting","defenseType":"reflex","condition":"vs attacks of opportunity","toggleable":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"]}}}
{"_id":"77c897590b4000f6","name":"Slicer Team","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Use Computer checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use Computer","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_synergy","skill_use_computer","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain bonuses on Use Computer checks when near allies."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"conditional_skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Slicer Team: +3 bonus to useComputer checks when the near-allies condition is confirmed.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"slicer-team","skillKeys":["useComputer"],"value":3,"type":"untyped","requiresContextFlags":["nearAllies"],"description":"Slicer Team: +3 when near supporting allies."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Use Computer checks when near allies."},"effects":[{"_id":"42e2b97a-7c7f-419c-ae1d-42e6080cb792","name":"Slicer Team","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Slicer Team","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.slicer_team"}}}
{"_id":"77dba0a49c63e42d","name":"Biotech Surgery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can install Bio-Implants onto a living being. The surgical procedure takes 1 hour of uninterrupted work, after which you must make a DC 20 Treat Injury check. If the check succeeds, the prosthesis is installed correctly. If the check fails, the prosthesis is not installed properly; however, you can try again after another uninterrupted hour of surgery.","prerequisite":"Trained in Treat Injury","special":"You can install Bio-Implants on yourself, but you take a -5 penalty on the Treat Injury check. If you have the Surgical Expertise Feat, you can install a Bio-Implant in 10 minutes instead of 1 hour.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":17,"tags":["defense","feat","general","healing","skill_treat_injury","support","survivability","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Surgery</p>\n<p>You can perform the surgical procedures necessary to graft Biotech components onto living flesh, similar to those used by the Yuuzhan Vong.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Treat Injury</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can install Bio-Implants onto a living being. The surgical procedure takes 1 hour of uninterrupted work, after which you must make a DC 20 Treat Injury check. If the check succeeds, the prosthesis is installed correctly. If the check fails, the prosthesis is not installed properly; however, you can try again after another uninterrupted hour of surgery.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can install Bio-Implants on yourself, but you take a -5 penalty on the Treat Injury check. If you have the Surgical Expertise Feat, you can install a Bio-Implant in 10 minutes instead of 1 hour.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"treatinjury"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Biotech Surgery"}]},"shortSummary":"Install a Bio-Implant on a living being.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Treat Injury","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Surgery"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.biotech_surgery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Surgery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7bc21d4a74b95be5","name":"Crush","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"If you successfully Pin an opponent with a Grapple attack (see Pin Feat for more details), you can immediately deal bludgeoning damage to it equal to your Unarmed damage or claw damage, whichever is greater.","prerequisite":"Pin, Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["control","feat","force","grapple","offense","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crush</p>\n<p>You can deal damage to a target that you&#x27;ve Grappled.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Pin, Base Attack Bonus +1</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you successfully Pin an opponent with a Grapple attack (see Pin Feat for more details), you can immediately deal bludgeoning damage to it equal to your Unarmed damage or claw damage, whichever is greater.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Crush"}]},"shortSummary":"Deal Unarmed or Claw damage to a Pinned opponent.","prerequisitesText":"Pin, Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crush"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.crush","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crush","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7cd5ebe725910cb2","name":"Weapon Specialization","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with the selected weapon group.","prerequisite":"Soldier level 4, Weapon Focus with selected weapon group","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","general","weapon_mastery","choice_required","immediate_choice","weapon_choice","choice_source_prerequisite"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"damage.weapon","value":2,"type":"untyped","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Weapon Specialization: +2 damage with selected Weapon Focus target","predicates":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"]}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"execution_mapped_phase6","choiceKind":"weapon_specialization","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.weapon_specialization","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.weapon_specialization","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","derivesFrom":["weapon_focus"],"consumes":"weapon_focus","provides":"weapon_specialization","effectTarget":"damage.weapon","effectValue":2},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with the selected weapon group."},"effects":[{"_id":"58919a68-86ab-4cc5-b2e8-4f7b712e1ff2","name":"Weapon Specialization","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.damageBonus.rifles","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Weapon Specialization","effectType":"combat_bonus","flagType":"Weapon Specialization"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"requiresImmediateChoice":true}}}
{"_id":"7d8366d0481d76e2","name":"Trench Warrior","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you are adjacent to a wall or object that provides you with Cover from your target's ranged attacks, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on your attack rolls against that target.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["cover_play","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trench_Warrior</p>\n<p>You have experience fighting in the trenches, and you know how to use cover to your attack advantage.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you are adjacent to a wall or object that provides you with Cover from your target&#x27;s ranged attacks, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on your attack rolls against that target.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Trench Warrior"}]},"shortSummary":"When you have Cover against an enemy's ranged attacks, gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls against that enemy.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trench_Warrior"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.trench_warrior","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trench_Warrior","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7de37c473be72f87","name":"Imperial Military Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, as a Free Action on your turn, you can negate any one Mind-Affecting effect targeting or currently affecting you.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":19,"tags":["background_opportunity","faction_training","feat","general","military","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Imperial_Military_Training</p>\n<p>You have been instilled with the sense of discipline and loyalty demanded by the Empire.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Once per encounter, as a Free Action on your turn, you can negate any one Mind-Affecting effect targeting or currently affecting you.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Imperial Military Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Negate one Mind-Affecting effect per encounter.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Imperial_Military_Training"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.imperial_military_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Imperial_Military_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7df64382f1a0a892","name":"Overwhelming Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You must spend two Swift Actions in the same round to activate this Feat. If your target attempts to use a Talent, Feat, or other ability to negate your attack (Such as Block, Deflect, or Vehicular Combat), the target takes a -5 penalty to any attack rolls or Skill Checks it makes to negate the attack. This effect applies to the next attack you make before the end of the same round.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":26,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Overwhelming_Attack</p>\n<p>You know how to get your attacks past enemy defenses, making sure they strike true.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You must spend two Swift Actions in the same round to activate this Feat. If your target attempts to use a Talent, Feat, or other ability to negate your attack (Such as Block, Deflect, or Vehicular Combat), the target takes a -5 penalty to any attack rolls or Skill Checks it makes to negate the attack. This effect applies to the next attack you make before the end of the same round.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Overwhelming Attack"}]},"shortSummary":"Any attempt to negate your attack takes a -5 penalty on the attack roll or Skill Check.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Overwhelming_Attack"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.overwhelming_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Overwhelming_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"80805c30ea6dd11e","name":"Aiming Accuracy","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you Aim at a target as a Full-Round Action (instead of two Swift Actions), you gain a +5 bonus to your next attack made with a weapon with which you are proficient in the following round against that target. The target must remain in your line of sight.","prerequisite":"Droid, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":18,"tags":["feat","full_round_action","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger&#x27;s Guide to Droids</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aiming_Accuracy</p>\n<p>When you have time to analyze your shot, your shooting accuracy has a precision that only a machine can achieve.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you Aim at a target as a Full-Round Action (instead of two Swift Actions), you gain a +5 bonus to your next attack made with a weapon with which you are proficient in the following round against that target. The target must remain in your line of sight.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Aiming Accuracy"}]},"shortSummary":"After aiming as a Full-Round Action, gain a +5 on next weapon attack.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aiming_Accuracy"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.aiming_accuracy","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aiming_Accuracy","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"80c52cf7838095c1","name":"Return Fire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Select one Exotic Weapon or Weapon Group for which you possess the Weapon Focus feat. Once per encounter as a Reaction, you can make a single ranged attack with the chosen weapon against an enemy that misses you with a ranged attack, provided you have line of sight to the enemy.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 15, Quick Draw, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","special":"This Feat does not apply to Vehicle Weapons or Heavy Weapons. You must have your weapon in hand to use this Feat. You can take this Feat multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Weapon Group or Exotic Weapon.\n\nCombined Feat (Combat Reflexes): You may use this Feat a number of times during an encounter equal to your Dexterity bonus, but no more than once during a given enemy's turn.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["counterattack","feat","general","new_action","offense","offense_ranged","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Return_Fire</p>\n<p>When someone takes a shot at you and misses, you retaliate with a shot of your own.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 15, Quick Draw, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Select one Exotic Weapon or Weapon Group for which you possess the Weapon Focus feat. Once per encounter as a Reaction, you can make a single ranged attack with the chosen weapon against an enemy that misses you with a ranged attack, provided you have line of sight to the enemy.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>This Feat does not apply to Vehicle Weapons or Heavy Weapons. You must have your weapon in hand to use this Feat. You can take this Feat multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Weapon Group or Exotic Weapon.</p>\n<p>Combined Feat (Combat Reflexes): You may use this Feat a number of times during an encounter equal to your Dexterity bonus, but no more than once during a given enemy&#x27;s turn.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":15}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Return Fire"}]},"shortSummary":"You may make a single ranged attack as a Reaction to a ranged attack against you that misses.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 15, Quick Draw, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Return_Fire"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.return_fire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Return_Fire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"821e127ba3b83c1a","name":"Multi-Grab","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Standard Action, you may make a Grab attack against two targets adjacent to you (roll a separate attack against each target). You must have two empty hands to use this Feat.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Grab</p>\n<p>You may Grab two opponents at once.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>As a Standard Action, you may make a Grab attack against two targets adjacent to you (roll a separate attack against each target). You must have two empty hands to use this Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Multi-Grab"}]},"shortSummary":"You may Grab two opponents as a Standard Action.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Grab"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.multi_grab","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Grab","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
