{"_id":"b1970c18996d44dd","name":"Unified Squadron","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Pilot checks checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Pilot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_pilot","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","vehicle","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain bonuses on Pilot checks checks when near allies."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"conditional_skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Unified Squadron: +3 bonus to pilot checks when the near-allies condition is confirmed.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"unified-squadron","skillKeys":["pilot"],"value":3,"type":"untyped","requiresContextFlags":["nearAllies"],"description":"Unified Squadron: +3 when near supporting allies."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Pilot checks checks when near allies."},"effects":[{"_id":"318db08e-459c-45f8-b86e-3e67175b59ee","name":"Unified Squadron","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Unified Squadron","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.unified_squadron"}}}
{"_id":"b2296a4d5cef8a61","name":"Frightful Presence","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a standard action, you may make a Persuasion check to intimidate all enemies within 6 squares. On a success, targets move -1 step down the condition track.","prerequisite":"Charisma 15","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["control","feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Frightful Presence"}]},"shortSummary":"As a standard action, you may make a Persuasion check to intimidate all enemies within 6 squares."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"b26497554169ac38","name":"Instinctive Defense","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"On your turn, as a Free Action, you can spend a Force Point to increase all of your Defenses by 2 until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Cannot be a Droid","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":25,"tags":["defense","feat","force_point_spend","general","resource_spend","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Defense</p>\n<p>You naturally know how to avoid attacks and defend your mind and body when The Force is with you.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Cannot be a Droid</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>On your turn, as a Free Action, you can spend a Force Point to increase all of your Defenses by 2 until the start of your next turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"ACTIVE","subType":"RESOURCE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Instinctive Defense"}],"resourceRules":{"forcePoints":[{"type":"SPEND_FOR_TEMP_DEFENSE","value":2,"duration":"1round","description":"Spend a Force Point to increase all Defenses by +2 for 1 round."}]}},"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"resource":"forcePoint"},"shortSummary":"Spend a Force Point to increase all Defenses by +2 for 1 round.","prerequisitesText":"Cannot be a Droid","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Defense"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.instinctive_defense","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Defense","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b3965f7a31f310ec","name":"Cybernetic Surgery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can install Cybernetic Devices on living beings. The surgical procedure takes 1 hour of uninterrupted work, after which you must make a DC 20 Treat Injury check. If the check succeeds, the Cybernetic Device is installed correctly. If the check fails, the device is not properly installed; however, you can try again after another uninterrupted hour of surgery.","prerequisite":"Trained in Treat Injury","special":"You can install a Cybernetic Prosthesis or Energy-Binding Prosthesis on yourself, but you take a -5 penalty on the Treat Injury skill check (you cannot install a Rhen-Orm Biocomputer or a Subelectronic Converter on yourself). If you have the Surgical Expertise Feat, you can install a Cybernetic Device in 10 minutes instead of 1 hour.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["defense","feat","general","healing","skill_treat_injury","support","survivability","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Cybernetic_Surgery</p>\n<p>You can perform the surgical procedures necessary to graft cybernetic components onto living flesh.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Treat Injury</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can install Cybernetic Devices on living beings. The surgical procedure takes 1 hour of uninterrupted work, after which you must make a DC 20 Treat Injury check. If the check succeeds, the Cybernetic Device is installed correctly. If the check fails, the device is not properly installed; however, you can try again after another uninterrupted hour of surgery.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can install a Cybernetic Prosthesis or Energy-Binding Prosthesis on yourself, but you take a -5 penalty on the Treat Injury skill check (you cannot install a Rhen-Orm Biocomputer or a Subelectronic Converter on yourself). If you have the Surgical Expertise Feat, you can install a Cybernetic Device in 10 minutes instead of 1 hour.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"treatinjury"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Cybernetic Surgery"}]},"shortSummary":"Install a Cybernetic Prosthesis onto a living being.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Treat Injury","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Cybernetic_Surgery"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.cybernetic_surgery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Cybernetic_Surgery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b3984239e21c64ca","name":"Suppression Fire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use the Aid Another action to impose a penalty to an enemy's attack rolls and your attack roll exceeds the target's Will Defense, that enemy must end its next turn in a position where it has Cover from you if possible. Targets whose level is equal to or higher than your Character Level are immune to the effect of Suppression Fire. This is a Mind-Affecting Fear effect.","prerequisite":"Strength 13, Burst Fire, Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Threats of the Galaxy","page":21,"tags":["area_pressure","control","feat","general","grapple","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Suppression_Fire</p>\n<p>You can lay down a hail of blaster fire to pin your enemies.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength 13, Burst Fire, Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you use the Aid Another action to impose a penalty to an enemy&#x27;s attack rolls and your attack roll exceeds the target&#x27;s Will Defense, that enemy must end its next turn in a position where it has Cover from you if possible. Targets whose level is equal to or higher than your Character Level are immune to the effect of Suppression Fire. This is a Mind-Affecting Fear effect.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Suppression Fire"}]},"shortSummary":"You can lay down a hail of blaster fire to pin your opponents.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13, Burst Fire, Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Suppression_Fire"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.suppression_fire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Suppression_Fire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b3dfdfd783cf16be","name":"A Few Maneuvers","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When piloting a Vehicle of Colossal size or smaller, you grant a +2 dodge bonus to your Vehicle's Reflex Defense. Furthermore, if you are the target of a missile or torpedo attack and the attack roll misses by 5 or more, the projectile self-destructs harmlessly.","prerequisite":"Dodge, Vehicular Combat","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Threats of the Galaxy","page":20,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/A_Few_Maneuvers</p>\n<p>You can weave, juke, and roll to avoid enemy fire in the thick of combat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dodge, Vehicular Combat</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When piloting a Vehicle of Colossal size or smaller, you grant a +2 dodge bonus to your Vehicle&#x27;s Reflex Defense. Furthermore, if you are the target of a missile or torpedo attack and the attack roll misses by 5 or more, the projectile self-destructs harmlessly.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] A Few Maneuvers"}]},"shortSummary":"You can weave, juke, and roll to avoid enemy fire in the thick of combat.","prerequisitesText":"Dodge, Vehicular Combat","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/A_Few_Maneuvers"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.a_few_maneuvers","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/A_Few_Maneuvers","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b4c1dbb468777c09","name":"Rebel Military Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you use the Running Attack feat to move both before and after making an attack, you gain a +2 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Running Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["background_opportunity","faction_training","feat","general","military","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rebel_Military_Training</p>\n<p>You are well versed in the hit-and-run tactics used by The Rebel Alliance and know how to use your mobility to avoid retribution.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Running Attack</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Whenever you use the Running Attack feat to move both before and after making an attack, you gain a +2 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense until the start of your next turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Rebel Military Training"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a dodge bonus to Reflex Defense when using Running Attack.","prerequisitesText":"Running Attack","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rebel_Military_Training"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.rebel_military_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rebel_Military_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b531781f373c3031","name":"Master of Disguise","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 insight bonus to your Deception check when creating a Deceptive Appearance. In addition, you can rush the process by taking a -2 penalty to the Deception check.","prerequisite":"Trained in Deception, Charisma 13","special":"","normalText":"When you rush the creation of a Deceptive Appearance, you take a -10 penalty to your Deception check.","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":21,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Master_of_Disguise</p>\n<p>You are adept at creating convincing disguises in remarkably short periods of time.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Deception, Charisma 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You gain a +5 insight bonus to your Deception check when creating a Deceptive Appearance. In addition, you can rush the process by taking a -2 penalty to the Deception check.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>When you rush the creation of a Deceptive Appearance, you take a -10 penalty to your Deception check.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Master of Disguise"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain +5 to creating a Deceptive Appearance or a Forged Document, and reduce the penalty for rushing.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Deception, Charisma 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Master_of_Disguise"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.master_of_disguise","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Master_of_Disguise","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b573d4f48af37b42","name":"Attack Combo (Ranged)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you hit a single target with two consecutive ranged attacks during the same turn, any additional ranged attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +3","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":15,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Ranged)</p>\n<p>Your damage-dealing ability improves after hitting a single target with successive ranged attacks.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +3</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you hit a single target with two consecutive ranged attacks during the same turn, any additional ranged attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":3}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Attack Combo (Ranged)"}]},"shortSummary":"Deal +1 die of damage on ranged attacks until the end of your next turn after hitting an enemy with two ranged attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +3","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Ranged)"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.attack_combo_ranged","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Ranged)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b5a8d5899e02139c","name":"Far Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use a ranged weapon against targets at Short, Medium, or Long Range, the Range category is considered one less. In other words, you take no penalty on ranged attack rolls made at Short Range, a -2 penalty on ranged attack rolls made against targets at Medium Range, and a -5 penalty on ranged attack rolls made against targets at Long Range.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot","special":"","normalText":"When making a ranged attack roll, a character takes a -2 penalty against targets at Short Range, a -5 penalty against targets at Medium Range, and a -10 penalty against targets at Long Range.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Far_Shot</p>\n<p>You are better at shooting distant foes.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you use a ranged weapon against targets at Short, Medium, or Long Range, the Range category is considered one less. In other words, you take no penalty on ranged attack rolls made at Short Range, a -2 penalty on ranged attack rolls made against targets at Medium Range, and a -5 penalty on ranged attack rolls made against targets at Long Range.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>When making a ranged attack roll, a character takes a -2 penalty against targets at Short Range, a -5 penalty against targets at Medium Range, and a -10 penalty against targets at Long Range.</p>\n<h4>Additional Far Shot Effects</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p>This Feat works normally with Vehicle Weapons. However, if you are using a Missile or a Torpedo and you miss with your attack roll, the projectile does not gain the benefit of this Feat for the second attack roll.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Far Shot"}]},"shortSummary":"Range penalties for Short-, Medium-, and Long-ranged attacks are reduced.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Far_Shot"},"effects":[{"_id":"95e717d6-e35f-4987-aa9f-df3ad86b403f","name":"Far Shot","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Far Shot","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Far Shot"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.far_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Far_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b60e581b6c102cfc","name":"Long Haft Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use a Lightsaber Pike or a Long-Handle Lightsaber, you can attack with both ends of the weapon, treating it as a double weapon.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Jedi Academy Training Manual","page":29,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Long_Haft_Strike</p>\n<p>You have learned to take advantage of oversized Lightsabers, turning them into double weapons.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you use a Lightsaber Pike or a Long-Handle Lightsaber, you can attack with both ends of the weapon, treating it as a double weapon.</p>\n<h4>Homebrew Long Haft Strike Data</h4>\n<p>This Homebrew Content has not been reviewed in a meaningful manner. If you wish to review this content yourself, then see Untested for more details.</p>\n<p>Long Shaft Strike data created by Wikia user Chellewalker (formally Wikia user Lukewarner).</p>\n<p>A character may apply the effects of the Long Haft Strike Feat to any melee weapon one size category larger than themselves. For example, a Small character may use this Feat with Medium melee weapons, and Medium characters may use this Feat with Large melee weapons.</p>\n<p>Characters may attack with both ends of the weapon as a Full-Round Action, but both attack rolls have a -10 penalty; certain Feats and Talents can reduce these penalties. The bludgeoning damage dealt by this bonus damage is determined by the chart below.</p>\n<table class=\"swse-rules-table\"><tbody><tr><th>CHARACTER SIZE</th><th>WEAPON SIZE</th><th>DAMAGE</th></tr><tr><td>Small</td><td>Medium</td><td>1d4</td></tr><tr><td>Medium</td><td>Large</td><td>1d6</td></tr><tr><td>Large</td><td>Huge</td><td>1d8</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Long Haft Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"You can wield a long-handled weapon as a Double Weapon.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Long_Haft_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.long_haft_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Long_Haft_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b648515a5e8dd612","name":"Tireless Squad","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Endurance checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Endurance","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_endurance","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain bonuses on Endurance checks when near allies."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"conditional_skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Tireless Squad: +3 bonus to endurance checks when the near-allies condition is confirmed.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"tireless-squad","skillKeys":["endurance"],"value":3,"type":"untyped","requiresContextFlags":["nearAllies"],"description":"Tireless Squad: +3 when near supporting allies."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Endurance checks when near allies."},"effects":[{"_id":"173e71a3-9001-4b47-95b2-9143a098273a","name":"Tireless Squad","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Tireless Squad","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.tireless_squad"}}}
{"_id":"b754b5e064c20cc0","name":"Improvised Weapon Mastery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You treat all Improvised Weapons as Simple Weapons, and you can use them without penalty and with Talents and Feats designed for use with Simple Weapons. You also deal an additional 1d6 points of damage on a successful hit.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improvised_Weapon_Mastery</p>\n<p>You use Improvised Weapons with true skill.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You treat all Improvised Weapons as Simple Weapons, and you can use them without penalty and with Talents and Feats designed for use with Simple Weapons. You also deal an additional 1d6 points of damage on a successful hit.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"grants":[{"category":"PROFICIENCY","proficiencyType":"weapon","proficiencies":["improvised"],"description":"Weapon proficiency: improvised weapons treated as simple"}],"status":"improvised_weapon_mastery_partial","description":"Improvised Weapon Mastery: Treat improvised weapons as Simple Weapons (proficiency automation). +1d6 damage and feat/talent interaction remain GM-enforced.","ruleNotes":[{"id":"improvised-weapon-mastery-damage","label":"+1d6 Damage","text":"+1d6 damage with improvised weapons (manual tracking).","mechanical":true,"gmEnforced":true},{"id":"improvised-weapon-mastery-talents","label":"Feat/Talent Interaction","text":"Feats and talents designed for Simple Weapons apply to improvised weapons when treated as simple (manual determination).","mechanical":true,"gmEnforced":true}]},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"feat","feat":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)"}],"_source":"metadata-update"},"shortSummary":"Treat Improvised Weapons as Simple Weapons, deal +1d6 points of damage.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improvised_Weapon_Mastery"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.improvised_weapon_mastery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improvised_Weapon_Mastery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b7d60764c9cb6bbd","name":"Hew","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use Power Attack, you ignore an amount of damage reduction equal to your base attack bonus.","prerequisite":"Power Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Hew"}]},"shortSummary":"When you use Power Attack, you ignore an amount of damage reduction equal to your base attack bonus."},"effects":[{"_id":"2ea228d9-ede6-403b-8eea-201927f387e3","name":"Hew","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Hew","effectType":"negation","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"b7f51561e60fefe6","name":"Mission Specialist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose one Skill in which you are Trained. Allies who are not Trained in that Skill gain a +2 competence bonus to the Skill while they are within 12 squares of you.","prerequisite":"None","special":"You can select this Feat multiple times. Each time you select this Feat, it applies to a different Skill. Only allies who have the Force Sensitivity feat gain this bonus to Use the Force checks.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general","knowledge","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mission_Specialist</p>\n<p>You are so good with certain Skills that others around you benefit from your guidance and example.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Choose one Skill in which you are Trained. Allies who are not Trained in that Skill gain a +2 competence bonus to the Skill while they are within 12 squares of you.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can select this Feat multiple times. Each time you select this Feat, it applies to a different Skill. Only allies who have the Force Sensitivity feat gain this bonus to Use the Force checks.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Mission Specialist"}]},"shortSummary":"Grant bonus to allies' Untrained Skill Checks with a particular Skill.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mission_Specialist"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.mission_specialist","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mission_Specialist","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"b9d4eb946079b555","name":"Mechanical Martial Arts","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you successfully damage an enemy with an Unarmed Attack, the enemy takes a -5 penalty to all melee attack rolls and damage rolls until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Droid, Martial Arts I, Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"If you strike an organic enemy while using this Feat during an Attack of Opportunity, the penalty lasts until the start of the enemy's next turn.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":22,"tags":["feat","general","martial_style","offense_melee","tech","unarmed","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger&#x27;s Guide to Droids</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mechanical_Martial_Arts</p>\n<p>You know how to inflict pain using your metal appendages when fighting in Unarmed combat against organic enemies.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid, Martial Arts I, Base Attack Bonus +1</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you successfully damage an enemy with an Unarmed Attack, the enemy takes a -5 penalty to all melee attack rolls and damage rolls until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>If you strike an organic enemy while using this Feat during an Attack of Opportunity, the penalty lasts until the start of the enemy&#x27;s next turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Mechanical Martial Arts"}]},"shortSummary":"Give an enemy a -5 penalty on attack and damage rolls for one round after striking it in Unarmed combat.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Martial Arts I, Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mechanical_Martial_Arts"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.mechanical_martial_arts","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mechanical_Martial_Arts","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"baff0da30d0bc8ee","name":"Force of Personality","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can use either your Wisdom modifier or your Charisma modifier to determine your Will Defense.","prerequisite":"Charisma 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":23,"tags":["ability_charisma","ability_wisdom","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_of_Personality</p>\n<p>As a result of your self-confidence and conviction, your will is strong.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charisma 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can use either your Wisdom modifier or your Charisma modifier to determine your Will Defense.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Force of Personality"}]},"shortSummary":"Use Wisdom or Charisma to determine Will Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Charisma 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_of_Personality"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.force_of_personality","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_of_Personality","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"bb16070b5fdfccf4","name":"Mon Calamari Shipwright","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Reroute Power more quickly and without the risk of failure.","prerequisite":"Mon Calamari","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","species","species_opportunity","species_prerequisite_phase10"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-mon-calamari"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Reroute Power more quickly and without the risk of failure."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Mon Calamari Shipwright"}]},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"species","species":["Mon Calamari"]}],"_source":"phase10_species_prereq"},"shortSummary":"Reroute Power more quickly and without the risk of failure."},"effects":[{"_id":"cdf1b6ac-e96a-47ce-b26b-4b35a6e0d0fb","name":"Mon Calamari Shipwright","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Mon Calamari Shipwright","effectType":"special","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.mon_calamari_shipwright"}}}
{"_id":"bb7a952715116e00","name":"Improved Opportunistic Trickery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever an opponent provokes an Attack of Opportunity from you, once per turn you can sacrifice the attack to reduce the target's Reflex Defense by 5 until the end of the target's next turn.","prerequisite":"Combat Reflexes, Opportunistic Trickery","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":20,"tags":["feat","general","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Opportunistic_Trickery</p>\n<p>When your opponent lets down its guard, you open it up to additional attacks.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Combat Reflexes, Opportunistic Trickery</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Whenever an opponent provokes an Attack of Opportunity from you, once per turn you can sacrifice the attack to reduce the target&#x27;s Reflex Defense by 5 until the end of the target&#x27;s next turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Improved Opportunistic Trickery"}]},"shortSummary":"Sacrifice Attack of Opportunity to reduce target's Reflex Defense by 5.","prerequisitesText":"Combat Reflexes, Opportunistic Trickery","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Opportunistic_Trickery"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.improved_opportunistic_trickery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Opportunistic_Trickery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"bcc7f3fe56008a28","name":"Unleashed","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can activate Unleashed Abilities by spending a Destiny Point. You must also have the Force Sensitivity Feat in order to activate Force Unleashed Abilities for Force Powers and Force Talents.","prerequisite":"Have a Destiny, Receive the Gamemaster's Approval","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":37,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unleashed</p>\n<p>You gain access to Unleashed Abilities. If you have the Force Sensitivity Feat, you also gain access to Force Unleashed Abilities.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Have a Destiny, Receive the Gamemaster&#x27;s Approval</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can activate Unleashed Abilities by spending a Destiny Point. You must also have the Force Sensitivity Feat in order to activate Force Unleashed Abilities for Force Powers and Force Talents.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Unleashed"}]},"shortSummary":"Unlocks Unleashed Abilities.","prerequisitesText":"Have a Destiny, Receive the Gamemaster's Approval","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unleashed"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.unleashed","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unleashed","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"be1346b0cfb5ea78","name":"Regenerative Healing","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Regain more Hit Points (but more slowly) when you catch a Second Wind.","prerequisite":"Trandoshan","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["durability","feat","hit_points","racial","recovery","second_wind","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-trandoshan"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Regain more Hit Points (but more slowly) when you catch a Second Wind."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Regenerative Healing"}]},"shortSummary":"Regain more Hit Points (but more slowly) when you catch a Second Wind."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.regenerative_healing"}}}
{"_id":"be1b2f8015c971a5","name":"Increased Agility","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You increase your Climb Speed, Swim Speed and Jump distance by +2 squares and do not lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense when climbing.","prerequisite":"Conditioning","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","skill_climb","skill_jump","skill_swim","skill_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Increased_Agility</p>\n<p>Due to your own natural abilities or specific training, you move faster or farther than normal when climbing, jumping, and swimming.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Conditioning</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You increase your Climb Speed, Swim Speed and Jump distance by +2 squares and do not lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense when climbing.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Increased Agility"}]},"shortSummary":"Increase Climb Speed, Swim Speed, and Jump distance by 2 squares.","prerequisitesText":"Conditioning","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Increased_Agility"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.increased_agility","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Increased_Agility","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"bee76d01da40677d","name":"Lightning Reflexes","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus to your Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958","f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","type":"untyped","value":2,"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Migrated from AE system.defenses.reflex.bonus"}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus to your Reflex Defense."},"effects":[{"name":"Lightning Reflexes","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.defenses.reflex.bonus","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":20}],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"defense-bonus","defense":"reflex","migratedToPassive":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bf6c01fa590a3f75","name":"Biotech Specialist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can modify a Biotech device, suit of armor, weapon, or Vehicle so that it gains a specific trait. You can perform only one modification at a time. Unless noted otherwise, you cannot grant more than one benefit to a single device, suit of armor, weapon, or Vehicle, and you cannot apply the same benefit more than once.\n\nBefore beginning the modification, you must pay one tenth the cost of the device, suit of armor, weapon, or Vehicle you wish to modify or 1,000 credits, whichever is more. Completing the modification requires one day per 1,000 credits of the modification cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 20 Mechanics check; you can't Take 10 or Take 20 on this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent making the modification, and the object doesn't gain the desired trait. However, you may start over if you wish.\n\nDue to the specialized nature of Biotechnology, only other characters with the Biotech Specialist Feat can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification. At the end of the modification process, they can make a Mechanics check to aid your check.\n\nThe market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item + double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed attempts).\n\nARMOR TRAITS | BENEFIT\nAgile Armor | The armor's maximum Dexterity bonus increases by 1.\nFortifying Armor | The armor's Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense increases by 1.\nProtective Armor | The armor's Armor bonus to Reflex Defense increases by 1.\nDEVICE TRAITS | BENEFIT\nAdd Device to Creature | Alter a bioengineered creature to accept a biotech or standard technological enhancement such as a miniaturized Sensor Pack.\nEnhanced Strength | Increase the device's Strength score by 2.\nImproved Durability | The device's Damage Reduction increases by 1, and it gains extra Hit Points equal to one-quarter of its maximum Hit Points.\nMastercraft Device | Skill Checks made using the device gain a +1 Equipment bonus, or the device's existing Equipment bonus increases by 1.\nVEHICLE TRAITS | BENEFIT\nDovin Basal Enhancement | Increase the effects of a Dovin Basal to grant one of the following benefits to a Starship: +1 additional square of movement at Starship Scale, +2 SR, or +1 die of damage when using a Dovin Basal.\nEnhanced Dexterity | Increase the Vehicle's Dexterity score by 2.\nImproved Speed | Increase the Vehicle's Speed by one-quarter of its base Speed (minimum 1 square).\nWEAPON TRAITS | BENEFIT\nImproved Accuracy | The weapon gains a +1 Equipment bonus on attack rolls.\nImproved Damage | The weapon deals +2 points of damage with a successful hit. If the weapon has a damage multiplier (for example, 6d10x2), apply the extra damage before applying the multiplier.\nSelective Fire | An Autofire -only ranged weapon can be set to fire single shots, or a single-shot weapon can be made to have an Autofire mode. This cannot be applied to weapons that have a Burst radius or Splash radius.","prerequisite":"Trained in Mechanics","special":"This Feat allows you to make Treat Injury checks on Biotechnology without the normal -5 penalty.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":16,"tags":["feat","general","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Specialist</p>\n<p>You can make custom modifications to Biotech -based armor, weapons, Vehicles, and similar devices.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Mechanics</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can modify a Biotech device, suit of armor, weapon, or Vehicle so that it gains a specific trait. You can perform only one modification at a time. Unless noted otherwise, you cannot grant more than one benefit to a single device, suit of armor, weapon, or Vehicle, and you cannot apply the same benefit more than once.</p>\n<p>Before beginning the modification, you must pay one tenth the cost of the device, suit of armor, weapon, or Vehicle you wish to modify or 1,000 credits, whichever is more. Completing the modification requires one day per 1,000 credits of the modification cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 20 Mechanics check; you can&#x27;t Take 10 or Take 20 on this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent making the modification, and the object doesn&#x27;t gain the desired trait. However, you may start over if you wish.</p>\n<p>Due to the specialized nature of Biotechnology, only other characters with the Biotech Specialist Feat can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification. At the end of the modification process, they can make a Mechanics check to aid your check.</p>\n<p>The market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item + double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed attempts).</p>\n<table class=\"swse-rules-table\"><tbody><tr><th>ARMOR TRAITS</th><th>BENEFIT</th></tr><tr><td>Agile Armor</td><td>The armor&#x27;s maximum Dexterity bonus increases by 1.</td></tr><tr><td>Fortifying Armor</td><td>The armor&#x27;s Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense increases by 1.</td></tr><tr><td>Protective Armor</td><td>The armor&#x27;s Armor bonus to Reflex Defense increases by 1.</td></tr><tr><td>DEVICE TRAITS</td><td>BENEFIT</td></tr><tr><td>Add Device to Creature</td><td>Alter a bioengineered creature to accept a biotech or standard technological enhancement such as a miniaturized Sensor Pack.</td></tr><tr><td>Enhanced Strength</td><td>Increase the device&#x27;s Strength score by 2.</td></tr><tr><td>Improved Durability</td><td>The device&#x27;s Damage Reduction increases by 1, and it gains extra Hit Points equal to one-quarter of its maximum Hit Points.</td></tr><tr><td>Mastercraft Device</td><td>Skill Checks made using the device gain a +1 Equipment bonus, or the device&#x27;s existing Equipment bonus increases by 1.</td></tr><tr><td>VEHICLE TRAITS</td><td>BENEFIT</td></tr><tr><td>Dovin Basal Enhancement</td><td>Increase the effects of a Dovin Basal to grant one of the following benefits to a Starship: +1 additional square of movement at Starship Scale, +2 SR, or +1 die of damage when using a Dovin Basal.</td></tr><tr><td>Enhanced Dexterity</td><td>Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Dexterity score by 2.</td></tr><tr><td>Improved Speed</td><td>Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Speed by one-quarter of its base Speed (minimum 1 square).</td></tr><tr><td>WEAPON TRAITS</td><td>BENEFIT</td></tr><tr><td>Improved Accuracy</td><td>The weapon gains a +1 Equipment bonus on attack rolls.</td></tr><tr><td>Improved Damage</td><td>The weapon deals +2 points of damage with a successful hit. If the weapon has a damage multiplier (for example, 6d10x2), apply the extra damage before applying the multiplier.</td></tr><tr><td>Selective Fire</td><td>An Autofire -only ranged weapon can be set to fire single shots, or a single-shot weapon can be made to have an Autofire mode. This cannot be applied to weapons that have a Burst radius or Splash radius.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>This Feat allows you to make Treat Injury checks on Biotechnology without the normal -5 penalty.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"745a5686d6f21e8c"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Biotech Specialist"}]},"shortSummary":"Make custom modifications to Yuuzhan Vong Biotech.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Mechanics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Specialist"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.biotech_specialist","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Specialist","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"bf71e5f4171547ef","name":"Instinctive Perception","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain a temporary Force Point when your Perception reroll is lower.","prerequisite":"Zabrak","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","force_point_spend","racial","reroll","resource_spend","skill_perception","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-zabrak"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Gain a temporary Force Point when your Perception reroll is lower."},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Instinctive Perception"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a temporary Force Point when your Perception reroll is lower."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.instinctive_perception"}}}
{"_id":"c01f64239af7705d","name":"Extra Rage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can Rage one additional time per day.","prerequisite":"Rage Species Trait","special":"You can take this Feat multiple times; each time you take this Feat, you can Rage one additional time per day.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase9","feat","general","offense_melee","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Rage</p>\n<p>You can fly into a Rage more often.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rage Species Trait</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can Rage one additional time per day.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can take this Feat multiple times; each time you take this Feat, you can Rage one additional time per day.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rage_rule_phase9","description":"Extra Rage: +1 additional Rage use per day.","rules":[{"type":"RAGE_USES_BONUS","value":1,"description":"Rage one additional time per day."}]},"shortSummary":"Rage one additional time per day.","prerequisitesText":"Rage Species Trait","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Rage"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.extra_rage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Rage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c060d4cb33df501a","name":"Angled Throw","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When throwing a Grenade or grenadelike weapon, you can attempt to bounce it off a wall or other surface close to your target. If you attack roll exceeds a Reflex Defense of 15, you ignore Cover and Improved Cover (but not Total Cover) with your attack.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":32,"tags":["area_pressure","cover_play","feat","general","grenade","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Angled_Throw</p>\n<p>Your amazing throws bounce Grenades off walls into open hatches or through congested battle zones.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When throwing a Grenade or grenadelike weapon, you can attempt to bounce it off a wall or other surface close to your target. If you attack roll exceeds a Reflex Defense of 15, you ignore Cover and Improved Cover (but not Total Cover) with your attack.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Angled Throw"}]},"shortSummary":"Ignore Cover with Grenades and grenadelike weapons.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Angled_Throw"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.angled_throw","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Angled_Throw","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c0bd186e6fb23619","name":"Knock Heads","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"After successfully using the Multi-Grab Feat against two targets that are both adjacent to you and each other, you can immediately knock their heads together, dealing automatic bludgeoning damage to each creature equal to 1d6 plus your Strength modifier. When comparing the damage to each creature's Damage Threshold, treat their Damage Thresholds as if they were 5 points lower. Both creatures are still considered Grabbed at the end of using this Feat.","prerequisite":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Multi-Grab","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knock_Heads</p>\n<p>You knock two opponents&#x27; heads together in unarmed combat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Multi-Grab</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>After successfully using the Multi-Grab Feat against two targets that are both adjacent to you and each other, you can immediately knock their heads together, dealing automatic bludgeoning damage to each creature equal to 1d6 plus your Strength modifier. When comparing the damage to each creature&#x27;s Damage Threshold, treat their Damage Thresholds as if they were 5 points lower. Both creatures are still considered Grabbed at the end of using this Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13},{"type":"attribute","ability":"str","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Knock Heads"}]},"shortSummary":"You may knock two opponents' heads together after a successful Multi-Grab.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Multi-Grab","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knock_Heads"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.knock_heads","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knock_Heads","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c120ef1fe27225af","name":"Controlled Rage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You enter a Rage as a Free Action. Your Rage ends 1 round after you declare it is finished.","prerequisite":"Rage Species Trait","special":"You may not use this Feat to extend the number of rounds of Rage available to your character.","normalText":"You must use a Swift Action to begin a Rage and may not end it at will.","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":33,"tags":["action_economy","execution_mapped_phase9","feat","free_action","general","offense_melee","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Controlled_Rage</p>\n<p>You have learned to channel your Rage.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rage Species Trait</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You enter a Rage as a Free Action. Your Rage ends 1 round after you declare it is finished.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>You must use a Swift Action to begin a Rage and may not end it at will.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You may not use this Feat to extend the number of rounds of Rage available to your character.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rage_rule_phase9","description":"Controlled Rage: enter Rage as a free action and end it at will.","rules":[{"type":"RAGE_ACTION_MODE","activation":"free","canEndAtWill":true,"description":"Enter Rage as a free action and end Rage at will."}]},"shortSummary":"Enter Rage as a Free Action, and end Rage at will.","prerequisitesText":"Rage Species Trait","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Controlled_Rage"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.controlled_rage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Controlled_Rage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c180eee7d3bc29b2","name":"Precise Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can shoot or throw a ranged weapon at an opponent engaged in melee combat with one or more of your allies without taking the standard -5 penalty.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot","special":"If another Vehicle fires into a Dogfight, it takes a -5 penalty on its attack roll, unless the Gunner has the Precise Shot feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["accuracy","anti_cover","feat","feat_chain","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Precise_Shot</p>\n<p>You are skilled at timing your ranged attacks so that you don&#x27;t hit your ally by mistake.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can shoot or throw a ranged weapon at an opponent engaged in melee combat with one or more of your allies without taking the standard -5 penalty.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>If another Vehicle fires into a Dogfight, it takes a -5 penalty on its attack roll, unless the Gunner has the Precise Shot feat.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Precise Shot: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"preciseShot","label":"Precise Shot","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","suppresses":["firingIntoMeleePenalty"],"summary":"Ignore firing-into-melee penalties where the attack engine applies them."}]},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"No -5 penalty for shooting into melee.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Precise_Shot"},"effects":[{"_id":"77e126ab-16c9-4116-9d67-b5550c007b1b","name":"Precise Shot","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Precise Shot","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Precise Shot"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.precise_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Precise_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c238f3f722689a3a","name":"Pin","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you succeed on a Grappling attack and your opponent fails the opposed Grapple check, your opponent is automatically Pinned until the start of your next turn. A Pinned creature can't move or take any Actions while Pinned, and it loses its Dexterity bonus (if any) to Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"You cannot use the Pin and Trip Feats during the same round. You can use the Pin and Crush Feats in the same round, however.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["ability_dexterity","control","feat","general","grapple"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pin</p>\n<p>You are skilled at immobilizing Grappled foes.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +1</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>If you succeed on a Grappling attack and your opponent fails the opposed Grapple check, your opponent is automatically Pinned until the start of your next turn. A Pinned creature can&#x27;t move or take any Actions while Pinned, and it loses its Dexterity bonus (if any) to Reflex Defense.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You cannot use the Pin and Trip Feats during the same round. You can use the Pin and Crush Feats in the same round, however.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Pin"}]},"shortSummary":"Grappled opponent is Pinned for one round, can't move, and and loses its Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pin"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.pin","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pin","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c2538c3a906700ae","name":"Forceful Blast","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a Grenade or Thermal Detonator, compare the result of your attack roll to the target's Fortitude Defense. If your result equals or exceeds the target's Fortitude Defense, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a Free Action.\n\nIf the Grenade deals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can't move a target that's being Grabbed or Grappled, and you can't move a target into a solid object or into another creature's Fighting Space.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons), Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["area_pressure","feat","force","grenade","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Blast</p>\n<p>You can position your Grenade attacks such that they blast creatures away from the center of the explosion.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons), Base Attack Bonus +1</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a Grenade or Thermal Detonator, compare the result of your attack roll to the target&#x27;s Fortitude Defense. If your result equals or exceeds the target&#x27;s Fortitude Defense, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a Free Action.</p>\n<p>If the Grenade deals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can&#x27;t move a target that&#x27;s being Grabbed or Grappled, and you can&#x27;t move a target into a solid object or into another creature&#x27;s Fighting Space.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Forceful Blast"}]},"shortSummary":"Move a target damaged by your Grenade attack.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons), Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Blast"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.forceful_blast","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Blast","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c2da9691c1bb9742","name":"Focused Rage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While Raging, you can use Skills that require patience and concentration, at a -5 penalty.","prerequisite":"Rage Species Trait, Controlled Rage","special":"","normalText":"While Raging, you cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force.","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase9","feat","general","offense_melee","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Focused_Rage</p>\n<p>You retain better focus when enraged.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rage Species Trait, Controlled Rage</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>While Raging, you can use Skills that require patience and concentration, at a -5 penalty.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>While Raging, you cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rage_rule_phase9_partial","description":"Focused Rage: permits patience/concentration skill uses while raging at a -5 penalty when those rolls are flagged by the caller.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"focused-rage-patience-penalty","skillKeys":["any"],"value":-5,"type":"rage","requiresContextFlags":["raging","requiresPatience"],"description":"Focused Rage: use patience-based skills while raging at -5."}],"rules":[{"type":"RAGE_ALLOW_PATIENCE_SKILLS","penalty":-5,"description":"When Raging, use skills that require patience at a -5 penalty."}]},"shortSummary":"When Raging, use Skills that require patience at a -5 penalty.","prerequisitesText":"Rage Species Trait, Controlled Rage","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Focused_Rage"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.focused_rage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Focused_Rage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c301a0f533f15ce4","name":"Point Blank Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You get a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls with ranged weapons against opponents within Point-Blank Range.","prerequisite":"None","special":"This Feat works normally with Vehicle Weapons. However, if you are using a Missile or a Torpedo and you miss with your attack roll, the projectile does not gain the benefit of this Feat for the second attack roll.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["accuracy","damage_scaling","feat","feat_chain","general","offense","offense_ranged","mapped_phase_1","passive_state"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Point-Blank_Shot</p>\n<p>You are skilled at making well-placed shots with ranged weapons at Point-Blank Range.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You get a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls with ranged weapons against opponents within Point-Blank Range.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>This Feat works normally with Vehicle Weapons. However, if you are using a Missile or a Torpedo and you miss with your attack roll, the projectile does not gain the benefit of this Feat for the second attack roll.</p>\n<h4>Additional Rangefinders and Targeting Scopes</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War</p>\n<p>Under most circumstances, a character with the Point-Blank Shot Feat receives a bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls only when the target is within his or her weapon&#x27;s Point-Blank Range.</p>\n<p>The use of a Targeting Scope does not change how far your target is from you, so taking an Aim Action with a Targeting Scope on a Blaster Rifle to attack a target that is 50 squares away does not give you the +1 bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls that you would receive if the target were within 30 squares. This is the same for the Rangefinder upgrade, which negates the penalty for attacking a target that is at Short Range.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack.bonus","value":1,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged","range.within-point-blank"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Point Blank Shot: +1 ranged attack within point-blank range"},{"target":"damage.ranged","value":1,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged","range.within-point-blank"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Point Blank Shot: +1 ranged damage within point-blank range"}]},"shortSummary":"+1 bonus on ranged attacks and damage against foes within Point-Blank Range.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Point-Blank_Shot"},"effects":[{"name":"Point Blank Shot","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.attackBonus.ranged","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":20},{"key":"system.damageBonus.ranged","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":20}],"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"conditional","condition":"within 6 squares"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Point-Blank_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c41814601364b643","name":"Weapon Focus","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group, you gain a +1 bonus on all attack rolls you make using the selected Exotic Weapon or weapon group.","prerequisite":"Proficient with Chosen Weapon","special":"You can gain this Feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the Feat, it applies to a new Exotic Weapon or weapon group.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["accuracy","feat","general","weapon_mastery","choice_required","immediate_choice","weapon_choice","choice_source_prerequisite"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Focus</p>\n<p>You are especially good at using particular weapons.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Proficient with Chosen Weapon</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group, you gain a +1 bonus on all attack rolls you make using the selected Exotic Weapon or weapon group.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You can gain this Feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the Feat, it applies to a new Exotic Weapon or weapon group.</p>\n<h4>Additional Weapon Focus Effects</h4>\n<p>Combined Feat (Weapon Finesse): When you are wielding a single one-handed weapon for which you have Weapon Focus, you can treat that weapon as a Light Weapon.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack.bonus","value":1,"type":"untyped","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Weapon Focus: +1 attack with selected proficient weapon group or exotic weapon","predicates":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"]}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"execution_mapped_phase6","choiceKind":"weapon_focus","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.weapon_focus","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.weapon_focus","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","derivesFrom":["weapon_proficiency"],"consumes":"weapon_proficiency","provides":"weapon_focus","effectTarget":"attack.bonus","effectValue":1},"shortSummary":"+1 bonus on attack rolls with chosen weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Proficient with Chosen Weapon","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Focus"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.weapon_focus","requiresImmediateChoice":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Focus","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c51d23038e2862e6","name":"Coordinated Barrage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you Aid Another ally's attack, for every 3 points that the ally's attack roll beats the target's Reflex Defense, the attack deals +1 die of damage. The maximum number of bonus damage dice the attack receives is equal to the number of allies with this Feat that aided on the attack roll or +5 dice, whichever is lower.","prerequisite":"Coordinated Attack, Base Attack Bonus +5","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Barrage</p>\n<p>When you combine fire with an ally, your barrage can have devastating results on the attacker.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Coordinated Attack, Base Attack Bonus +5</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you Aid Another ally&#x27;s attack, for every 3 points that the ally&#x27;s attack roll beats the target&#x27;s Reflex Defense, the attack deals +1 die of damage. The maximum number of bonus damage dice the attack receives is equal to the number of allies with this Feat that aided on the attack roll or +5 dice, whichever is lower.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":5}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Coordinated Barrage"}]},"shortSummary":"Allow an ally to deal more damage when you aid their attack.","prerequisitesText":"Coordinated Attack, Base Attack Bonus +5","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Barrage"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.coordinated_barrage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Barrage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c58e69ff5adb5e71","name":"Recall","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per day, you can reroll any check for a Knowledge Skill that you are Trained in, using the better result.","prerequisite":"Trained in at least one Knowledge Skill","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":36,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","knowledge","reroll","skill_knowledge","skill_synergy","utility","skill_reroll","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recall</p>\n<p>You know a lot of details in your area of knowledge, but don&#x27;t always remember them immediately.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in at least one Knowledge Skill</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Once per day, you can reroll any check for a Knowledge Skill that you are Trained in, using the better result.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"atleastoneknowledgeskill"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"skill_reroll_phase8","description":"Recall: reroll a Knowledge skill check and keep the better result.","skillRerolls":[{"id":"recall","skillKeys":["knowledge","knowledgeBureaucracy","knowledgeGalacticLore","knowledgeLifeSciences","knowledgePhysicalSciences","knowledgeSocialSciences","knowledgeTactics","knowledgeTechnology"],"outcome":"keepBetter","label":"Recall","description":"Recall: reroll a Knowledge skill check and keep the better result."}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll Knowledge skill check, keeping the better result.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in at least one Knowledge Skill","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recall"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.recall","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recall","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c7c99a77ebee1c0c","name":"Dual Weapon Mastery II","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a Full Attack Action, you take a -2 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 15, Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"If you use a Full Attack Action to make more than one attack on your turn, you take a -10 penalty on all attack rolls for the round.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["action_economy","dual_wield","feat","general","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_II</p>\n<p>You are a master at fighting with two weapons and double weapons.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 15, Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a Full Attack Action, you take a -2 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>If you use a Full Attack Action to make more than one attack on your turn, you take a -10 penalty on all attack rolls for the round.</p>\n<h4>Additional Dual Weapon Mastery II Effects</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy</p>\n<p>Vehicle Weapons cannot be used in one hand, so this Feat has no effect on them.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":15},{"type":"bab","min":6}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Dual Weapon Mastery II"}]},"shortSummary":"Take a -2 penalty on attacks when attacking with two weapons, or both ends of a double weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 15, Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_II"},"effects":[{"_id":"fa217f33-b718-45d3-b256-9226da60389d","name":"Dual Weapon Mastery II","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Dual Weapon Mastery II","effectType":"special","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.dual_weapon_mastery_ii","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_II","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c9522152ffa425f9","name":"Knock Prone","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You may attempt to knock an opponent prone with a melee attack. If successful, the target falls prone.","prerequisite":"Int 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","knock_prone","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee","target.is-prone"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Knock Prone"}]},"shortSummary":"You may attempt to knock an opponent prone with a melee attack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee","target.is-prone"]}}}
{"_id":"c973e43c85382068","name":"Autofire Assault","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When wielding a weapon for which you possess the Weapon Focus Feat, and you target the same area with an Autofire attack that you made an Autofire attack against on your last turn, the penalty on the Autofire attack is reduced to -2 (-1 if using a Braced Autofire -only weapon or the Controlled Burst Talent) and you deal +1 die of damage on a hit.","prerequisite":"Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","special":"This Feat cannot be used with the Autofire Sweep Feat or the Burst Fire Feat.","normalText":"A -5 penalty applies to Autofire attack rolls, and there are no bonuses for consecutive rounds of fire in the same squares.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":23,"tags":["area_pressure","autofire","feat","full_attack_synergy","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Autofire_Assault</p>\n<p>Your Autofire attacks are devastating when focused in a single area for multiple rounds.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When wielding a weapon for which you possess the Weapon Focus Feat, and you target the same area with an Autofire attack that you made an Autofire attack against on your last turn, the penalty on the Autofire attack is reduced to -2 (-1 if using a Braced Autofire -only weapon or the Controlled Burst Talent) and you deal +1 die of damage on a hit.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>A -5 penalty applies to Autofire attack rolls, and there are no bonuses for consecutive rounds of fire in the same squares.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>This Feat cannot be used with the Autofire Sweep Feat or the Burst Fire Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Autofire Assault"}]},"shortSummary":"Decrease penalty on Autofire attack and inflict extra damage when sustaining fire in the same squares in consecutive rounds.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Autofire_Assault"},"effects":[{"_id":"870f5168-26b8-487a-8255-fbf32ddc06ff","name":"Autofire Assault","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.combat.autofireDamageBonus","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Autofire Assault","effectType":"damage_bonus"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.autofire_assault","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Autofire_Assault","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"caad1a8c13bf01a1","name":"Withdrawal Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When taking this Feat, select a single Exotic Weapon (Melee) or melee weapon group with which you are proficient. When wielding that chosen Exotic Weapon (Melee) or melee weapon from the chosen group, adjacent opponents may not Withdraw from squares you threaten. They may still make Acrobatics checks to Tumble as normal.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +5","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":30,"tags":["feat","general","mobility","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Withdrawal_Strike</p>\n<p>Your enemies do not escape easily.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +5</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When taking this Feat, select a single Exotic Weapon (Melee) or melee weapon group with which you are proficient. When wielding that chosen Exotic Weapon (Melee) or melee weapon from the chosen group, adjacent opponents may not Withdraw from squares you threaten. They may still make Acrobatics checks to Tumble as normal.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":5}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Withdrawal Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"Adjacent opponents can not use the Withdraw Action.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +5","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Withdrawal_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.withdrawal_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Withdrawal_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cab4954728195119","name":"Hyperblazer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When traversing the Hyperspace Tangle, you reduce by half the calculation time and penalties on Use Computer checks to Astrogate (See Hyperspace Navigation Challenges). You also reduce Hyperspace Mapping time by half when mapping new Hyperspace Routes.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use Computer","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":23,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","skill_synergy","skill_use_computer"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hyperblazer</p>\n<p>You are familiar with blazing new routes and navigating the tangled web of Hyperspace in The Unknown Regions.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Use Computer</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When traversing the Hyperspace Tangle, you reduce by half the calculation time and penalties on Use Computer checks to Astrogate (See Hyperspace Navigation Challenges). You also reduce Hyperspace Mapping time by half when mapping new Hyperspace Routes.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Hyperblazer"}]},"shortSummary":"Cut all calculation time and Use Computer penalties by half when making Use Computer checks for Astrogation in the Hyperspace tangle. Reduce Hyperspace mapping time by half.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Use Computer","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hyperblazer"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.hyperblazer","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hyperblazer","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cb6aea7e256e4c8c","name":"Improved Rapid Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using a Light Melee Weapon or Lightsaber with the Rapid Strike Feat, you can take a -5 penalty to your attack roll to gain +2 dice of damage on a successful strike.","prerequisite":"Rapid Strike","special":"This does not stack with the Rapid Strike Feat or extra damage provided by any source that does not stack with the Rapid Strike Feat (such as Mighty Swing). If you do not have a Dexterity of 13 or higher, the penalty to your attack roll is -10 instead of -5.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Rapid_Strike</p>\n<p>Your Rapid Strike is more effective with Light Melee Weapons.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rapid Strike</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When using a Light Melee Weapon or Lightsaber with the Rapid Strike Feat, you can take a -5 penalty to your attack roll to gain +2 dice of damage on a successful strike.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>This does not stack with the Rapid Strike Feat or extra damage provided by any source that does not stack with the Rapid Strike Feat (such as Mighty Swing). If you do not have a Dexterity of 13 or higher, the penalty to your attack roll is -10 instead of -5.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Improved Rapid Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"Trade -5 penalty on attack roll for +2 dice of damage when using a Light Melee Weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Rapid Strike","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Rapid_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.improved_rapid_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Rapid_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cbea70febcf834cd","name":"Burst of Speed","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Move Action, you can Move up to twice your speed. At the end of your movement, you move -1 step along the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"Trained in Endurance","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["action_economy","feat","general","mobility","move_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Burst_of_Speed</p>\n<p>You are capable of incredible bursts of speed.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Endurance</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>As a Move Action, you can Move up to twice your speed. At the end of your movement, you move -1 step along the Condition Track.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"35df8faa4878f2c5"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Burst of Speed"}]},"shortSummary":"Move Speed twice as Move Action.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Endurance","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Burst_of_Speed"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.burst_of_speed","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Burst_of_Speed","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ccb33e58342499a3","name":"Rapid Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using a melee weapon with which you are proficient, you may make two strikes as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"The effects of this feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the Mighty Swing Feat. If you do not have a Dexterity score of 13 or higher, increase the penalty to attacks to -5 when using this Feat with non-Light Weapons.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","feat_chain","general","lightsaber_compatible","offense","offense_melee","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Strike</p>\n<p>You make two quick strikes with a melee weapon as a single attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus +1</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When using a melee weapon with which you are proficient, you may make two strikes as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>The effects of this feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the Mighty Swing Feat. If you do not have a Dexterity score of 13 or higher, increase the penalty to attacks to -5 when using this Feat with non-Light Weapons.</p>\n</div>"},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Rapid Strike: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"rapidStrike","label":"Rapid Strike","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","attackModifier":-2,"damageDiceStepBonus":1,"summary":"Take -2 on a melee attack to deal +1 die of damage."}]},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"Take a -2 penalty on a melee attack roll to deal +1 die of damage.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.rapid_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ccc7a6e191e811a4","name":"Hobbling Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you would deal extra damage by using Sneak Attack, Rapid Shot, or Rapid Strike, you can reduce the target's Speed by 1 square until the end of the encounter, instead of dealing the extra damage.","prerequisite":"Sneak Attack or Rapid Shot or Rapid Strike.","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hobbling_Strike</p>\n<p>You know where to hit your enemy to slow it down.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Sneak Attack or Rapid Shot or Rapid Strike.</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Whenever you would deal extra damage by using Sneak Attack, Rapid Shot, or Rapid Strike, you can reduce the target&#x27;s Speed by 1 square until the end of the encounter, instead of dealing the extra damage.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Hobbling Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"Reduce the target's Speed instead of dealing damage.","prerequisitesText":"Sneak Attack or Rapid Shot or Rapid Strike.","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hobbling_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.hobbling_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hobbling_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cda6cb7b58f96a2f","name":"Acrobatic Dodge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, as a Reaction, if a melee attack misses you, you can immediately move into an adjacent square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13, Dodge, Mobility, Skill Focus (Acrobatics)","special":"You must be aware of the attacker to benefit from this Feat. You can use this Feat a second time during the encounter by spending a Force Point.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":19,"tags":["defense","feat","general","reaction","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Dodge</p>\n<p>When you react to an attack, your acrobatics training improves your mobility.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity 13, Dodge, Mobility, Skill Focus (Acrobatics)</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>Once per encounter, as a Reaction, if a melee attack misses you, you can immediately move into an adjacent square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity.</p>\n<h4>Special</h4>\n<p>You must be aware of the attacker to benefit from this Feat. You can use this Feat a second time during the encounter by spending a Force Point.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Acrobatic Dodge"}]},"shortSummary":"When a melee attack misses you, move into an adjacent square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13, Dodge, Mobility, Skill Focus (Acrobatics)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Dodge"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.acrobatic_dodge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Dodge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ce009e054ef1681f","name":"Implant Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You are not moved an extra step down the Condition Track when you would normally be moved down the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"Must possess an Implant","special":"","normalText":"Characters with an Implant move one extra step down the Condition Track when moved down the Condition Track for any reason, and take a -2 penalty to their Will Defense without this Feat.","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":26,"tags":["condition_track","feat","general","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Implant_Training</p>\n<p>You have acclimated your mind and body to the presence of a cybernetic implant.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Must possess an Implant</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You are not moved an extra step down the Condition Track when you would normally be moved down the Condition Track.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>Characters with an Implant move one extra step down the Condition Track when moved down the Condition Track for any reason, and take a -2 penalty to their Will Defense without this Feat.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[]},"resourceRules":{"damage":[{"type":"PREVENT_IMPLANT_CT_PENALTIES","status":"BLOCKED_NO_IMPLANT_SYSTEM","note":"This feat assumes an implant system that applies CT penalties. Currently, implants are equipment only; no implant-triggered CT penalty system exists. Feat is awaiting future implant system implementation.","blockedSince":"2026-05-11"}]},"shortSummary":"You don't move additional steps down the Condition Track due to your Implants.","prerequisitesText":"Must possess an Implant","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Implant_Training"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.implant_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Implant_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ce473e52f90b160a","name":"Improved Disarm","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 bonus on any melee attack roll made to Disarm an opponent. In addition, if you fail to Disarm an opponent, he doesn't get to make a free attack against you.","prerequisite":"Intelligence 13, Melee Defense","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Disarm</p>\n<p>You are skilled at Disarming opponents in melee combat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence 13, Melee Defense</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You gain a +5 bonus on any melee attack roll made to Disarm an opponent. In addition, if you fail to Disarm an opponent, he doesn&#x27;t get to make a free attack against you.</p>\n<h4>Additional Improved Disarm Effects</h4>\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide</p>\n<p>Combined Feat (Force Training): When you use the Force Disarm Force Power, you gain the +5 bonus from Improved Disarm on your Use the Force check as though you were making an attack roll.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":5,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Improved Disarm"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain +5 bonus on melee attacks to Disarm an opponent.","prerequisitesText":"Intelligence 13, Melee Defense","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Disarm"},"effects":[{"_id":"11028f88-1c7b-4f68-8cb6-352d73d94b1b","name":"Improved Disarm","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Improved Disarm","effectType":"combat_bonus","flagType":"Improved Disarm"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.improved_disarm","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Disarm","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ce946668c5b57410","name":"Harm’s Way","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a reaction, you may take damage dealt to an adjacent ally instead of them.","prerequisite":"Base attack bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":25,"tags":["defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["proximity.ally-nearby"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Harm’s Way"}]},"shortSummary":"As a reaction, you may take damage dealt to an adjacent ally instead of them."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.ally-nearby"]}}}
{"_id":"cefb9edb540745d6","name":"Multi-Targeting","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can use Swift Actions across more than one round to Aim at a target with a weapon with which you are proficient. You can attack different targets prior to the completion of your Aim Action. If the subject of your Aim is out of your line of sight for any reason, you lose your Aim and must start again.","prerequisite":"Droid, Intelligence 13","special":"","normalText":"You must normally use two consecutive Swift Actions in the same round to Aim.","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":23,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger&#x27;s Guide to Droids</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Targeting</p>\n<p>Your targeting system allows you to track multiple targets over time, negating Cover bonuses.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid, Intelligence 13</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>You can use Swift Actions across more than one round to Aim at a target with a weapon with which you are proficient. You can attack different targets prior to the completion of your Aim Action. If the subject of your Aim is out of your line of sight for any reason, you lose your Aim and must start again.</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>You must normally use two consecutive Swift Actions in the same round to Aim.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Multi-Targeting"}]},"shortSummary":"You can spread your Aim action across multiple consecutive rounds.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Intelligence 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Targeting"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.multi_targeting","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Targeting","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cf278001c780f3f9","name":"Momentum Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When riding a Beast as a Mount or on a Speeder Bike (as a passenger or a Pilot), you add +1 die of damage to any melee attacks if your Mount or Vehicle has already moved at least its speed this turn.","prerequisite":"Trained in Pilot or Ride","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Threats of the Galaxy","page":20,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Momentum_Strike</p>\n<p>You know how to put the full weight of your momentum into attacks while riding a Mount or a Speeder Bike.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained in Pilot or Ride</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When riding a Beast as a Mount or on a Speeder Bike (as a passenger or a Pilot), you add +1 die of damage to any melee attacks if your Mount or Vehicle has already moved at least its speed this turn.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Momentum Strike"}]},"shortSummary":"You know how to put the weight of your momentum into attacks while riding a Mount or Speeder Bike.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Pilot or Ride","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Momentum_Strike"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.momentum_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Momentum_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
